('http://oskarstalberg.com/Townscaper/', 'Townscaper', '', 'builds, devices, supported, townscaper, webgl, mobile', 'WebGL builds are not supported on mobile devices.', '2021-12-03', 'http://oskarstalberg.com/Townscaper/TemplateData/favicon.ico', 'oskarstalberg.com'),
('http://retro.ircx.net.pl/nt/mips/wx86/', 'WX86 rediscovered', '', 'wx86, windows, rediscovered, qemu, nt, 64bit, r4000, fx32, platform, probably, run', 'created 20180902, updated 20200411Such topic is probably worth more technical writing, but right now it\'s for pure fun.\nWX86 is a technology preview component for Windows NT4 back from 1996.\nHooks in PE32 executable loader inside NT executive were introduced with NT4 MIPS/PPC/Alpha, they are sort-of integrated with OS.\nFX!32 probably hooked in a different way... until Windows 2000 RC for Alpha shipped with FX!32 packaged in wx86.dll/wx86cpu.dll due to later agreements with DECWill it run on qemu-system-mips64el?\nMy quick and blind attempt at this: qemu.2.11.1.mips.r4000.64bit.patchpatched build of QEMU 2.11.1 for MacOS X Sierra 10.12', '2021-12-03', 'http://retro.ircx.net.pl/nt/mips/wx86/wx86_mips64.png', 'retro.ircx.net.pl'),
('https://9to5mac.com/2021/12/02/apple-commision-outside-of-the-app/', 'Apple legal filing indicates it intends to collect commission regardless of whether developers use IAP or a competing payments platform', 'Benjamin Mayo, Philips Hue Lights, The Easiest Way To Get Into Homekit, Apple Smart Home Tech. Great For Gifts., Iphone Wireless Charger, Inexpensive, Fast, Wireless Charger For Iphone.', 'regardless, app, payments, platform, iap, legal, developers, transactions, system, intends, links, allow, purchases, inapp, commission, apple, payment, filing, indicates, competing', 'Apple currently charges a 15-30% commission on in-app purchases and basically all digital goods purchases must use Apple’s In-App Purchase system.\nApple currently forbids apps from linking out to the web to offer an alternate payment system, outside of Apple’s purview.\nHowever, the Epic-Apple decision as it stands today will mean that Apple must relax that policy and allow external links.\nThe document reads that if the injunction were to go into effect, Apple could charge a commission on purchases made through such mechanisms.\nAs such, Apple also stresses the “substantial engineering” that it says is necessary to allow linking to other payment systems.', '2021-12-02', 'https://i1.wp.com/9to5mac.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2020/12/app-store-hero.jpg?resize=1200%2C628&quality=82&strip=all&ssl=1', '9to5mac.com'),
('https://abitgamey.substack.com/p/user-type-needs', 'User type needs', 'Phil Martin', 'socialisers, player, video, games, user, type, needs, players, types, game, post, apps, love', 'Bartle player typesRichard Bartle classified video game players according to their preferred actions in games.\nBy knowing where the majority of players fall in this model, developers can balance the focus of the game features to address these predominant needs; other player type needs getting less focus.\nWhile Bartle’s model applies to video game players, it can be used to help optimise designs for mobile apps in general.\nOther resourcesBartle’s player types for gamification by Interaction Design FoundationFree2Play: Making money from games you give away by Will Luton.\nUntil next Sunday, consider what type of Bartle user you are and the extent to which apps you use meet your needs.', '2021-12-03', 'https://cdn.substack.com/image/fetch/w_1200,c_limit,f_jpg,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3d73feab-934b-437d-a738-2b8c4ac8d195_787x321.jpeg', 'abitgamey.substack.com'),
('https://adventofcode.com', 'Advent of Code 2021', '', '2021, code, advent', '', '2021-12-03', 'https://adventofcode.com/favicon.png', 'adventofcode.com'),
