('https://cilium.io/blog/2021/12/01/cilium-service-mesh-beta/', 'Try eBPF-powered Cilium Service Mesh - join the beta program!', '', 'capabilities, traffic, cilium, mesh, beta, ebpfpowered, kubernetes, features, observability, try, join, service, sure, program', 'Cilium Service Mesh features eBPF-powered connectivity, traffic management, security and observability, and we’re inviting you to be amongst the first to try out these new capabilities as part of the Cilium Service Mesh Beta Program.\nThe term “Service Mesh” encompasses a wide range of features, including service discovery, encryption, service authentication, load balancing, observability, canary roll-outs and more.\nWe’d like feedback from an active group of Cilium users who can try out Cilium Service Mesh features and help us make sure we\'re providing a stable, performant service mesh.\nHowever, Cilium’s service mesh architecture is designed so that it can be integrated with any service mesh control plane and specification.\nThe intention is that core Cilium Service Mesh features will be ready for production use in Q1 2022.', '2021-12-01', 'https://cilium.io/static/b0307b499e327eb226dd4f58d2244f2e/d5ccc/sidecar-sweep.jpg', 'cilium.io'),
('https://codesandbox.io/post/sandpack-announcement', 'Introducing Sandpack', '', 'examples, running, sandpack, using, code, introducing, import, press, editor, custom, codesandbox', 'With this release, you can use Sandpack to power any live running code on your website.\nWho’s using Sandpack?\nThese are some of the projects using Sandpack for their own purpose: React Docs The new React Docs is using Sandpack for its examples and for the challenges.\nThe React team wanted to fully style and customize Sandpack for their new website, and with Sandpack they were able to customize everything.\nIf you’re using Sandpack, let us know and we’ll add you to our showcase!', '2021-12-03', 'https://codesandbox.io/static/banner-334bd8bf7d5b3cbecee8384ace8c3db1.png', 'codesandbox.io'),
('https://codigo.so', 'Learn to code', '', 'é, mod, escreva, sino, es, par, print, code, si, learn, mostrar, ímpar', 'para i = 1 ate 7 faca se i mod 2 == 0 entao escreva ( i, \"é par\" ) senao escreva ( i, \"é ímpar\" ) fimse fimparafor i = 1 to 7 do if i mod 2 == 0 then print ( i, \"is even\" ) else print ( i, \"is odd\" ) endif endforpara i = 1 hasta 7 hacer si i mod 2 == 0 entonces mostrar ( i, \"es par\" ) sino mostrar ( i, \"es impar\" ) finsi finpara', '2021-12-03', 'https://storage-codehub.s3.amazonaws.com/static/logos/iconcodigo.png', 'codigo.so'),
('https://cushychicken.github.io/rules-for-web-scrapers/', 'Some guidelines for writing web scrapers', '', 'stages, data, key, scraper, scraping, guidelines, writing, web, scrapers, script, way, job, ive, run', 'I’ve already written two job scraping systems to help ease the work of indexing jobs.\nHere’s some general rules I’ve come to hold for writing web scrapers and other ETL systems.\nThe way I’ve dealt with this is some exception handling code that tags weird results for human review:try : # rules[key] contains function pointer to a string transform function data_xfm [ key ] = rules [ key ]( data [ key ]) except Exception as e : logging .\nerror ( f \"Problem with keying/rule [key=\' { key } \']\" ) logging .\nI’d love to hear from you if there are any other useful methods or techniques you’ve used for web scraping and indexing.', '2021-12-02', 'https://cushychicken.github.io/assets/images/bg.svg', 'cushychicken.github.io'),
