('https://lemire.me/blog/2021/11/30/can-you-safely-parse-a-double-and-then-cast-to-a-float/', 'Can you safely parse a double when you need a float?', 'View All Posts Daniel Lemire, Joern Engel, Maynard Handley, Published By, Daniel Lemire, A Computer Science Professor At The University Of Quebec, Teluq .', 'round, float, c, string, end, need, parse, safely, results, double, char, systems, rounding', 'They are often referred to as float and double .\nOne parses a string to a float and the other function parses it to a double .\nWhy not just parse your string to a double value and cast it back to a float , if needed?\nIn other words, these functions are not equivalent:float parse1 ( const char * c ) { char * end ; return strtod ( c , & end ) ; } float parse2 ( const char * c ) { char * end ; return strtof ( c , & end ) ; }It is intuitive that if I first parse the number as a float and then cast it back to a double , I will have lost information in the process.\nIn the other direction, first parsing to a double and then casting back to a float , I can also lose information, although only a little bit due to the double rounding effect.', '2021-11-30', 'https://lemire.me/img/portrait2018facebook.jpg', 'lemire.me'),
('https://letsencrypt.status.io/pages/incident/55957a99e800baa4470002da/61a91b3eea08e105461a6418', 'Let\'s Encrypt Status', '', 'number, status, related, small, remediating, encrypt, utcmonitoring, registrations, window, lets, problems, remediated, occurred', 'December 2, 2021 21:15 UTC[Monitoring] We have identified and remediated the immediate problems affecting certificate issuance.\nWe are still remediating some problems related to data inconsistencies that occurred in a 30s window and affect a small number of registrations.', '2021-12-03', 'https://image.status.io/RVHRdNTftdLG.ico', 'letsencrypt.status.io'),
('https://lichess.org/blog/YafSBxEAACIAr0ZA/exact-exacting-who-is-the-most-accurate-world-champion', 'Exact, Exacting: Who is the Most Accurate World Champion?', '', 'champion, exacting, chess, played, games, engines, exact, championship, players, game, accurate, world, stockfish', 'The first step was deciding what counted as World Championship matches, then collecting them all, and compiling them.\nLikewise, the World Championship crown was briefly split between two competing organisations, and we had to consider how to treat that split.\nFrom a simple tabular form, it was clear that the initial claim was supported — and rather than the round 3 game being “one of the most accurate games played in a World Championship” it was actually the most accurate ever played in World Championship history.\nGenerally, all of the most accurate games played were relatively short.\nAll of the most accurate games would have been purely after the computer era, otherwise.', '2021-12-03', 'https://images.prismic.io/lichess/270665e7-7ea5-440a-8365-ee738090dd76_anatomy-gaa113f954_1280.png?auto=compress,format', 'lichess.org'),
('https://literaryreview.co.uk/visionary-of-bromley', 'The Young H G Wells: Changing the World by Claire Tomalin', 'Robert Douglas-Fairhurst, Claire Tomalin, Uilleam Blacker, Emma Garman, Philip Womack', 'long, wellss, little, claire, wells, writers, writing, young, world, tomalin, h, life, reason, g, changing', 'At the start of H G Wells’s 1909 novel Tono-Bungay, the narrator explains that most people continue through life in a neat line from beginning to end.\nIt was an output that would have been impressive coming from a whole team of writers, let alone one man.\nGeorge Orwell wrote after Wells’s death in 1946 that ‘We value H G Wells for Tono-Bungay, Mr Polly, The Time Machine, etc.\nTomalin also largely succeeds in justifying her second reason for looking closely at Wells’s later life.\nIt would be fascinating to know what she wrote about, but Tomalin does not tell us.', '2021-12-03', 'https://literaryreview.co.uk/wp-content/lr-files/2021/10/douglas-fairhurst-Wells-in-the-mid-1880s-with-gorilla-skull-and-skeleton-e1635763373328-600x405.jpg?1638489306', 'literaryreview.co.uk'),
('https://lithub.com/from-construction-to-teaching-seven-writers-on-their-day-jobs/', 'From Construction to Teaching: Seven Writers On Their Day Jobs', '', 'jobs, teaching, job, write, day, writers, way, writing, work, construction, im, seven, lot, life, love', 'I asked seven writers about their day jobs and how they manage to produce work in their off hours without losing their minds.\nAll that to say: I don’t think about writing often at my day job.\nWorking a day job that utilizes different muscles than writing keeps me from getting too burnt out when I toggle between the two.\nCurrently, I’m writing a column for Catapult exploring the immigrant experience through the lens of internet culture.\nI don’t really think about writing at my day job because it requires a lot of focus and mental energy.', '2021-11-30', 'https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/Everyone-a-Worker.png', 'lithub.com'),
('https://lunduke.substack.com/p/desqviewx-the-forgotten-mid-1990s', 'DESQview/X : The forgotten mid-1990s OS from the future', 'Bryan Lunduke', 'os, windows, x, dos, desqviewx, 31, applications, mid1990s, system, future, run, window, forgotten, x11', 'Then DESQview/X came along, in the 1990s, bringing a complete X11 (aka X Windows) graphical interface with it.\nThe ability to act as an X11 client (run X Windows applications running on another computer, such as a UNIX/Linux box).\nThe ability to act as an X11 server (allowing another X Windows client to run applications on the DESQview/X computer).\nAdd to that the ability to run DOS, Windows 3.1, and X Windows applications… it\'s just so much goshdarned fun.\nIf you have a DOS + Windows 3.1 + DESQview/X computer somewhere… you can run Windows 3.1 applications on your UNIX-y box, acting as an X11 client.', '2021-12-03', 'https://cdn.substack.com/image/fetch/w_1200,c_limit,f_jpg,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F45ce9e8f-2465-42e9-8e04-c5e9bc595798_640x480.jpeg', 'lunduke.substack.com'),
('https://multithreaded.stitchfix.com/blog/2021/10/14/functions-dags-hamilton/', 'Functions & DAGs: introducing Hamilton, a microframework for dataframe generation', '', 'dataframe, dag, example, functions, dags, column, generation, pd, introducing, code, hamilton, microframework, series, data, function', 'Series ) -> pd .\nSeries ) -> pd .\nSeries ) -> pd .\nSeries ) -> pd .\nSeries ) -> pd .', '2021-10-14', 'https://multithreaded.stitchfix.com/assets/posts/2021-10-14/hamiltondag.png', 'multithreaded.stitchfix.com'),
('https://nathanchance.dev/posts/cvise-lto-kernel-bug/', 'Reducing an LTO Linux kernel bug with cvise', '', 'build, bug, lto, error, c, cvise, linux, kernel, llvm, o2, source, reducing, file, flags, issue', 'My co-maintainer Nick Desaulniers wrote a great post about taking a several thousand line C file that exposed a compiler bug down to 12 lines with creduce .\nReproduce the bug with the latest compilerWe reproduced the bug with the latest Linux kernel development release but we used a released version of clang (13).\nI developed a Python LLVM build script ( build-llvm.py ) as part of tc-build to help with situations like this.\nIf you are reducing a build error on the object file, you can use the V=1 trick above to see the command.\nFirst, let’s try to build the source with gcc (as mentioned above, the Linux kernel requires optimizations to build so we add -O2 ):$ gcc -O2 -c -o /dev/null file.i ... $ echo $?', '2021-11-29', 'https://nathanchance.dev/images/favicon.ico', 'nathanchance.dev'),
('https://news.drweb.com/show/?i=14350', '«Doctor Web discovered vulnerabilities in children’s smart watches', '', 'vulnerabilities, doctor, number, web, devices, server, childrens, sms, q50, password, watches, discovered, watch, data, phone, smart, information', 'If a malicious third-party knows the watch’s password and SIM phone number, they can easily gain control over the device.\nBut they can still execute the command to verify the watch’s status and parameters without any limits, from any phone number.\nIf the attacker uses this command, the watch will send them the current administrator’s phone number, among other data about the device.\nTherefore, it is possible that during the manufacturing stage, malicious actors will plug Android smart watches with trojans or adware.\nThe summary table below shows the main vulnerabilities of the examined smart watches:Doctor Web has notified the manufacturers of uncovered vulnerabilities.', '2021-12-03', 'https://st.drweb.com/static/new-www/favicons/og-drweb-default.jpg?r=1', 'news.drweb.com'),
('https://news.harvard.edu/gazette/story/2021/12/harvard-epidemiologist-gives-early-impression-of-omicron/', 'Harvard’s Hanage discusses Omicron as first U.S. case is detected', 'Alvin Powell, Harvard Staff Writer', 'case, omicron, serious, thing, discusses, know, thats, detected, point, going, harvards, shots, hanage, south, variant', 'Pandemic scientists have spent the last few days racing to learn more about the coronavirus variant Omicron, which spread rapidly in South Africa last month and now has been detected in several other nations.\nThe more complicated thing is that we don’t yet know what it’s going to do in very highly vaccinated populations.\nWe know of a case from Israel in which a person who had received three shots transmitted to another person who had received three shots.\nIt’s early days, but it looks like that’s not going to be the case with Omicron.\nBut I think that it’s reasonable to say that whatever is going to happen with Omicron could happen really quickly.', '2021-12-01', 'https://news.harvard.edu/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/Hanage2500-1200x630.jpg', 'news.harvard.edu'),
('https://news.ucr.edu/articles/2021/11/30/study-links-high-cholesterol-cardiovascular-disease-plastics', 'Study links high cholesterol, cardiovascular disease to plastics', 'Author, Iqbal Pittalwala, November', 'health, plastics, ucr, study, risk, cardiovascular, zhou, high, phthalate, pxr, dchp, environmental, disease, links, cholesterol', 'Indeed, exposure to plastic-associated chemicals, such as base chemical bisphenol A and phthalate plasticizers, can increase the risk of human cardiovascular disease.\nIn a mouse study, the researchers found a phthalate — a chemical used to make plastics more durable — led to increased plasma cholesterol levels.\n“To our knowledge, our study is the first to show the effects of DCHP exposure on high cholesterol and cardiovascular disease risk in mouse models,” Zhou said.\nThe study was published in Environmental Health Perspectives, a top journal in the environmental health field.\nThe work was supported in part by the National Institute of Environmental Health Sciences, or NIEHS.', '2021-11-30', 'https://news.ucr.edu/sites/g/files/rcwecm1816/files/2020-08/nick-fewings--2lJGRIY5P0-unsplash.jpg', 'news.ucr.edu'),
('https://nixos.org/blog/announcements.html#21.11', 'Blog → Announcements', '', 'manual, list, nix, paper, blog, information, nixos, release, published, announcements, notes, released', 'BlogNixOS 21.11 released — Published on 30 Nov 2021NixOS 21.05 released — Published on 1 Jun 2021NixOS 20.09 released — Published on 27 Oct 2020NixOS 20.03 released — Published on 20 Apr 2020Hey everyone, I am worldofpeace, one of the release managers for 20.03.\nNixOS 19.09 released — Published on 09 Oct 2019NixOS 19.03 released — Published on 10 Apr 2019NixOS 18.09 released — Published on 06 Oct 2018Fastly supports NixOS — Published on 04 Oct 2018We are happy to announce that we have moved our binary cache to Fastly .\nAnd please consider submitting a talkNixOS 18.03 released — Published on 04 Apr 2018Nix 2.0 released — Published on 22 Feb 2018Nix 2.0 has been released.\nRead more…Nixpkgs 0.10 released — Published on 12 Nov 2006Nix 0.10.1 released — Published on 11 Nov 2006Nix 0.10.1 has been released.\nNixpkgs 0.9 released — Published on 03 Mar 2006PhD thesis defended — Published on 18 Feb 2006Nix 0.9.2 released — Published on 21 Oct 2005Nix 0.9.2 has been released released.', '2021-12-03', 'https://nixos.org/logo/nixos-lores.png', 'nixos.org'),
('https://nymag.com/article/2019/03/stephen-sondheim-on-how-to-do-a-crossword-puzzle.html', 'Stephen Sondheim on How to Do a Crossword Puzzle', 'Stephen Sondheim', 'puzzle, word, meaning, way, stephen, clue, puzzles, words, crossword, clues, answer, sondheim, york', 'There are crossword puzzles and crossword puzzles.\nOne is a reprint from the London Times and one is an American adaptation of a puzzle from The Listener, a weekly publication of the BBC.\nIn a British puzzle, definitions are called “clues.” This is not a pedantic distinction.\nEach clue, in actuality, is in two parts — a definition (i.e., a synonym) and an elliptical indication of the answer.\nSend completed diagram with name and address to Puzzle Editor, New York Magazine, 207 East 32nd Street, New York, New York 10016.', '2019-03-22', 'https://pyxis.nymag.com/v1/imgs/98d/e6d/f10b3b0c04714f7f38bffe5064bc1503e8-02-anniversary-lede.1x.rsocial.w1200.jpg', 'nymag.com'),
('https://o3de.org/blog/posts/o3de-2111-announcement/', 'Open 3D Foundation announces first major release of Open 3D Engine', 'Open Foundation', 'windows, developers, o3de, linux, 3d, system, engine, release, foundation, major, announces, open', 'O3DE’s first major release: Stable 21.11Today, the Open 3D Foundation (O3DF) and its members including Adobe, AWS, Huawei, Intel, and Niantic announced the O3DE Stable 21.11 release of the Apache 2.0-licensed Open 3D Engine project.\nIn addition to core engine capabilities, Open 3D Foundation members have contributed new capabilities to O3DE through the extensible Gem system.\nWhat is included in the latest release of Open 3D Engine?\nDoes the Open 3D Foundation hold an annual event for developers?\nIn October 2021, the Open 3D Foundation held its inaugural O3DECon event, with 36 sessions hosted by members of the Foundation.', '2021-12-03', 'https://o3de.org/img/logos/O3DE-Circle-Icon.png', 'o3de.org'),
