('https://payloadspace.com/the-us-c-band-spectrum-saga-explained/', 'The US C-Band Spectrum Saga, Explained', '', 'intelsat, satellite, ses, spectrum, midband, cba, saga, fcc, cband, operators, 5g, explained', 'The FCC is in the process of repurposing chunks of mid-band spectrum to accelerate 5G network rollouts.\nDec. 5 represents a key deadline for C-band satellite operators.\nIt’s a win for the satellite operators and their investors, but one that’s set against a messy and more complicated backdrop.\nIntelsat, SES, Eutelsat, and Telesat put aside their differences to form the C-Band Alliance (CBA) and lobby for a private C-band sale.\nAnd as CNET reports, a government/industry compromise—ie, a path forward for 5G mid-band rollouts—seems within reach.', '2021-11-30', 'https://payloadspace.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/tower-gd0106d545_1280.jpg', 'payloadspace.com'),
('https://photosauce.net/blog/post/what-makes-srgb-a-special-color-space', 'What Makes sRGB a Special Color Space?', '', 'makes, color, spec, space, profiles, values, special, whitepoint, rounded, encoding, given, srgb, matrix', 'There was a lot of hand-waving around the fact I was writing about the sRGB spec without having seen it, and a lot of the content in my post on that topic was inferred from information on Wikipedia and in the draft spec for sRGB.\nI want to clarify a few points from the specs for posterity, however, because sRGB is unlike any other ‘normal’ color space.\nsRGB defines an encoding rather than a color space in the traditional abstract sense.\nYou can’t treat sRGB like any other color space, because it’s not just a color space; it’s a specific encoding of a color space.\nI added a couple of video color spaces and new versions of the Adobe color spaces.', '2021-12-03', 'https://github.global.ssl.fastly.net/images/modules/logos_page/Octocat.png', 'photosauce.net'),
('https://pixelscommander.com/javascript/webgpu-computations-performance-in-comparison-to-webgl/', 'WebGPU computations performance in comparison to WebGL', 'Pixels Commander', 'performance, compute, main, webgpu, size, computations, pixels, data, does, webgl, matrix, comparison', 'WebGPU computations performance in comparison to WebGLWebGPU – the successor of WebGL, a brand new API to utilize GPUs in the browser.\nIn comparison to WebGL, WebGPU promises better performance and better compatibility with modern hardware, but the most recognizable feature of WebGPU is a special API for performing computations on GPU.\nWebGL does not have a special API for computation but still, there is a hack that makes it possible.\nWebGPU performance is significantly higher and gets to 3.5x faster compared to WebGL while it does not block the main thread.\nSmall but interesting fact – both WebGL / WebGPU require some time to warm up while JS goes full power straight away.', '2021-11-30', 'http://pixelscommander.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Matrices-multiplication-benchmark-1.png', 'pixelscommander.com'),
('https://platform.uno/blog/announcing-uno-platform-4-0-four-major-components-added/', 'Announcing Uno Platform 4-0. Four major components added.', 'Https, Platform.Uno Blog Author Uno-Platform-Team, Uno Platform Team, We Are The Uno Platform Team, More Posts Uno Platform Team', 'application, xaml, announcing, components, navigation, uno, code, platform, visual, toolkit, major, added, extensions, 40, studio', 'Four platform additions for speeding up application development announced: Visual Studio Code and Figma integration, Uno Platform Extensions and UI Toolkit.\nUno Platform ExtensionsTo help you bootstrap a new Uno Platform application and get started with proper architecture we are introducing Uno Extensions.\nControls from Uno Toolkit, Uno Navigation Extensions and Uno Reactive Extensions can be used when required.\nUno ToolkitIntroducing the Uno Toolkit, set of higher-level multiplatform components not offered out of the box by WinUI.\nIf you haven’t yet, please give Uno Platform a try – be it in Visual Studio 2022 or using the new Visual Studio Code plugin.', '2021-11-30', 'https://uno-website-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/30131916/Uno_4_BlogCover-1.jpg', 'platform.uno'),
