('https://research.nccgroup.com/2021/11/18/an-illustrated-guide-to-elliptic-curve-cryptography-validation/', 'An Illustrated Guide to Elliptic Curve Cryptography Validation', 'Paul Bottinelli, View All Posts Paul Bottinelli', 'points, subgroup, key, curve, validation, field, illustrated, point, cryptography, guide, coordinates, elliptic', 'The following blog posts are good resources on the topic: A (Relatively Easy To Understand) Primer on Elliptic Curve Cryptography by Nick Sullivan and Elliptic Curve Cryptography: a gentle introduction by Andrea Corbellini.\nIn elliptic curve cryptography, public keys are frequently sent between parties, for example to establish shared secrets using Elliptic curve Diffie–Hellman (ECDH).\nElliptic curve cryptography deals with the group of points on that elliptic curve, namely, a set of values satisfying the curve equation.\nConclusionWith the ubiquitous use of elliptic curve cryptography, failure to validate elliptic curve points can be a critical issue which is sadly still commonly uncovered during cryptography reviews.\nReferencesStandards for efficient cryptography, SEC 1: Elliptic Curve Cryptography, Section 3.2.2.1 Elliptic Curve Public Key Validation Primitive.', '2021-11-18', 'https://research.nccgroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/1-1.png', 'research.nccgroup.com'),
('https://riscv.org/announcements/2021/12/riscv-ratifies-15-new-specifications/', 'RISC-V International Ratifies 15 New Specifications, Opening Up New Possibilities for RISC-V Designs', 'Kim Mcmahon', 'international, data, open, designs, members, 15, specification, specifications, ratifies, riscv, opening, vector, cryptography, hypervisor, possibilities', 'ZURICH – Dec. 2, 2021 – RISC-V International, a global open hardware standards organization, today announced that RISC-V members have ratified 15 new specifications – representing more than 40 extensions – for the free and open RISC-V instruction set architecture (ISA).\n“In 2021, RISC-V International made huge leaps in our technical progress as we ratified 15 specifications that are critical for the future of computing,” said Krste Asanović, Chair of the RISC-V International Board of Directors.\n“The new RISC-V Vector specification will change the way people think about vector designs,” said Dave Ditzel, Founder and Executive Chairman of Esperanto Technologies.\nRISC-V International, a non-profit organization controlled by its members, directs the future development and drives the adoption of the RISC-V ISA.\nMembers of RISC-V International have access to and participate in the development of the RISC-V ISA specifications and related ecosystem.', '2021-12-02', 'https://riscv.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/RISC-V-Logo-jpeg.jpg', 'riscv.org'),
('https://sanfrancisco.cbslocal.com/2021/12/02/950009/', 'San Jose Teen Fails Driving Test Due To Tesla Regenerative Braking System', '', 'vehicles, jose, car, electric, drive, teen, tesla, regenerative, rosenblum, system, driving, san, braking, test, fails', 'Bryce Rosenblum, 16, embarked on his driving test alongside the DMV instructor in a Tesla Model 3, with regenerative braking activated in standard mode.\nThe Model 3’s regenerative braking system, like most EVs, activates when the driver eases pressure off the accelerator.\nAccording to the teen, the DMV instructor did not order him to deactivate the regenerative braking system.\nDMV’s Field Operations Division reviewed the drive test score sheet and has determined the drive test score will be revised as passing.\nIf a customer uses a PHEV or EV with regenerative braking for their drive test, staff has been advised to not postpone the test because the vehicle is equipped with a regenerative braking system and/or a one-pedal braking feature, follow existing drive test criteria when scoring the test, and the application of the regenerative braking system shall not be used as the sole reason to score a driving error or critical driving error.', '2021-12-02', 'https://sanfrancisco.cbslocal.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/15116056/2021/11/tesla-drive-test.jpg?w=1500', 'sanfrancisco.cbslocal.com'),
('https://santurcesoftware.com/making-web-sites-small', 'Making Websites Small', 'Santurce Software Llc', 'local, webp, kb, small, using, making, network, need, google, page, image, information, websites', 'There\'s a million ways to skin the cat of image resizing, whether you\'re using photoshop, gimp or a command line utility.\nThe last bit in your control is to ask yourself if your design needs a 1000px image or an image at all.\nDo we need 500 KB of javascript to display a static view of our business on google maps?\nSo create a small (webp) of your desired map and shave off a few hundred KB and some processing power that can be better spent elsewhere.\nUse the Coverage Tool to find javascript we\'re making clients download that we aren\'t actually utilizing.', '2021-12-03', 'https://santurcesoftware.com/static/img/webp/logo.png.webp/', 'santurcesoftware.com'),
('https://seattledataguy.substack.com/p/what-is-dbt-and-why-are-companies', 'What Is dbt and Why Are Companies Using It?', '', 'dbt, analysts, using, companies, analytics, company, work, devops, tool, data, help', 'Built by Fishtown Analytics (now dbt Labs), the data build tool or dbt is a command-line tool that allows data analysts to execute the “transform“ step in the Extract-Load-Transform pipeline.\nThey can do this by writing the dbt code in their preferred text editor and then running dbt from the common line.\nHere is an example:SourceDubbed as the “analytics engineering tool,” dbt is also open source and has become a regular part of the modern data stack of many companies.\nAlso, if you’re interested in reading some of our past issues such as Greylock VC and 5 Data Analytics Companies It Invests or The Future Of Data Science, Data EngineeringThen consider subscribing and supporting the community!\nOur team has had the opportunity to improve companies of all sizes data analytics strategy and infrastructure.', '2021-12-03', 'https://cdn.substack.com/image/fetch/w_1200,c_limit,f_jpg,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F62b7d3fd-5567-4da3-bafc-885b7f173891_1756x994.png', 'seattledataguy.substack.com'),
('https://semiengineering.com/why-its-so-difficult-and-costly-to-secure-chips/', 'Why It’s So Difficult — And Costly — To Secure Chips', 'Technical Paper Link, Kurt Shuler, Onri Jay Benally, Jan Hoppe, Boris Petrov, Rafael Roques, Mark D Lapedus, Ahsan Islam, Wes Neumeier, Pete Gasperini', 'data, devices, costly, secure, hardware, design, difficult, security, different, going, thats, chips, chip', 'But as more hardware is connected to the Internet, and to other hardware, chips are now a source of concern.\nOther industry segments are far less sophisticated when it comes to chip security.\n2: Secure chip architecture.\n“We have to be able to encrypt the data coming in and encrypt the data going out.\nCreating IoT Devices That Will Remain SecureStrategies for integrating secure devices into less-secure and legacy environments.', '2021-12-02', 'https://semiengineering.com/wp-content/uploads/Security2-1.png', 'semiengineering.com'),
('https://sharktastica.co.uk/articles/m4_story', 'Revealed: The story of the IBM Model M4 family', '', 'sleeves, key, keyboards, assembly, revealed, m41, family, keyboard, m4, numeric, model, ibm', '▲Revealed: The story of the IBM Model M4 familyPublished 03 July 2021Updated 23 November 2021Est.\nIn fact, here\'s a photo of an M4 and M4-1: Model M4 (left) and M4-1 (right) As shown, the difference between the M4 and M4-1 is the pointing stick and its left and right mouse buttons.\nModel M4-1 left and right mouse button mechanismsThe numeric keypad option Accompanying the M4 and M4-1 keyboards are the Model M4-1 numeric keypads.\nLexmark-branded Model M4 keyboard and Model M4-1 numeric keypad topside (credit: arkanoid) After Lexmark dropped keyboard production in April 1996, Key Tronic provided the immediate continuation of M4 production.\nThese IBM Space Saver Keyboards were succeeded by the full-travel rubber dome IBM Space Saver II Keyboard (model RT3200) produced for IBM by NMB.', '2021-12-03', 'https://sharktastica.co.uk/resources/images/articles/m4_story/m4_story.jpg', 'sharktastica.co.uk'),
