('https://siddhesh.substack.com/p/sopranos-finale', '[D] Endings and Non-Endings', '', 'ends, end, way, endings, episode, dont, going, nonendings, series, sopranos, tony, life, d', 'Different showrunners have thus tried different approaches towards endings, to varying degrees of success.\nThink again of the endings of Lost, Breaking Bad, Game of Thrones - so much happened in their final hours.\nBut then, in the last five minutes of this eight-year-long, eighty-six episode series, Tony walks into the diner where he’s decided to have dinner with his family.\nOn paper, The Sopranos ends in the simplest, cleanest way it possibly could: with the Sopranos having dinner together.\nBecause you only get to watch The Sopranos end for the first time once.', '2021-12-03', 'https://cdn.substack.com/image/fetch/w_1200,c_limit,f_jpg,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F89d1ae45-d246-4547-8e8d-c738bddd9a50_421x236.jpeg', 'siddhesh.substack.com'),
('https://signal.org/blog/become-a-signal-sustainer/', 'Become a Signal Sustainer', '', 'signal, sustainer, badge, using, payment, way, different, data, tech, model, kind', 'We’re building a different kind of tech – where your data stays in your hands – but we’re also building a different kind of tech organization.\nThis also means that as the sole beneficiaries of Signal, it is up to the people using Signal to sustain it.\nGive Signal a BoostIn addition to sustaining Signal, you can now also give Signal a boost any time: if a new feature makes you smile, if Signal makes your day a little better, or if you just want to give Signal a virtual high five.\nShould you stop using Signal, or uninstall the app, they will be automatically cancelled after the next cycle, which helps eliminate the “dark pattern” of subscriptions you’ve forgotten about.\nBecome a Signal sustainer; help change the way tech works so that it serves us all better.', '2021-12-03', 'https://signal.org/blog/images/subs-og.png', 'signal.org'),
('https://soundshader.github.io/vowels.html', 'Vowels as colored ACF images', '', 'vowels, audio, pictures, images, corresponds, openmid, mid, nearclose, vowel, acf, wikipedia, picture, colored', 'Vowels as colored ACF imageshttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Table_of_vowelsEach picture below corresponds to a vowel from the table above.\nIf a picture is missing, it’s because Wikipedia doesn’t provide a audio file for that vowel.\nRougly speaking, the radial coordinate corresponds to time, the angular coordinate corresponds to frequency and color correponds to pitch or musical note.\nFront Central Back Close Near-close Close-mid Mid Open-mid Near-open OpenRounded vowels.\nFront Central Back Close Near-close Close-mid Mid Open-mid OpenOther soundsAn annoyed and an angry cat:Singing birds:Noteshttps://soundshader.github.io/hss/?alog=4&bins=4096&cw=2048&ch=2048', '2021-12-03', 'https://soundshader.github.io/pics/rgb/256/obr.jpg', 'soundshader.github.io'),
('https://spectatorworld.com/book-and-art/life-rene-magritte-alex-danchev/', 'The life of René Magritte was even more surprising than his art', '', 'magritte, magrittes, georgette, painting, middleclass, art, éluard, rené, surprising, surrealists, philosophical, life, respectable', 'The Belgian painter René Magritte is a good example of huge talent pushed through a very narrow opening.\nHis origins lie firmly in what he has become — commercial art, posters and even wallpaper designs — and he was most inspired by art when it came to him in reproduction.\nHe liked respectable middle-class food.\nOn returning, they found that Magritte had depicted Apfel immaculately, but had rendered her completely bald with a polished skull.\nMagritte was a precise but not always a very elegant painter, attached to some extraordinary philosophical conundrums, expressed with great clarity.', '2021-12-03', 'https://3tu97y2w9w35k69i31phftc4-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/Magritte-Alamy.jpeg', 'spectatorworld.com'),
('https://sprocketfox.io/xssfox/2021/12/02/xrandr/', 'Ideal monitor rotation for programmers', '', 'transform, screen, need, monitor, hdmi3, angle, programmers, ideal, rotate, rotation, xrandr, output, display, little', 'This is a little tricky on macOS and Windows but on Linux we have all the freedom we need.\nOdd but ok.We have a little tool called xrandr (x resize and rotate).\nWe can use it to rotate the screen around to any angle we want.\nWebcam starts sliding awaySo this here I think is the best monitor orientation for software development.\nxrandr --output HDMI-3 --transform lots of numbers here takes a transformation matrix thats used to position the screen.', '2021-12-02', 'https://sprocketfox.io/apple-touch-icon.png', 'sprocketfox.io'),
('https://stokoe.me/summary-hammock-driven-development/', 'What is Hammock Driven Development?', '', 'youre, background, problem, solving, understand, need, dont, hammock, problems, development, mind, solve, driven', 'This is a summary of Rich Hickey\'s \'Hammock Driven Development\' talk.\nSolve problems, don\'t build features.\nTake the time to articulate the problem you\'re solving.\nWaking Mind vs Background MindHickey has a bunch of interesting stuff to say about what he calls your waking mind and your background mind.\nHe uses his waking mind to assign tasks to his background mind and to analyse its products.', '2021-11-25', 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1585664811087-47f65abbad64?crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&ixid=MnwxMTc3M3wwfDF8c2VhcmNofDR8fGhhbW1vY2t8ZW58MHx8fHwxNjM3ODM2ODYz&ixlib=rb-1.2.1&q=80&w=2000', 'stokoe.me'),
('https://supabase.com/blog/2021/12/01/realtime-row-level-security-in-postgresql', 'Realtime Postgres RLS now available on Supabase', '', 'rls, row, realtime, table, supabase, postgres, database, postgresql, changes, policy, level, security, available', 'Supabase projects have supported Row Level Security (RLS) for API authorization since our Auth launch.\nAs we were evaluating possible solutions to improve Realtime security, we looked to our Auth implementation as inspiration for a cohesive security system.\nBefore diving deeper into our Realtime RLS implementation, let\'s briefly cover how RLS works in PostgreSQL.\nRow Level Security PrimerWhen you need to control access to individual rows of data, PostgreSQL has you covered with Row Level Security (RLS) policies.\nTo get started, upgrade your Supabase JavaScript client to version v1.23.0 and launch your new PostgreSQL database today: database.newCreditsAuthored by:', '2021-12-01', 'https://supabase.com/images/blog/launch-week-three/realtime-row-level-security-in-postgresql/realtime-row-level-security-in-postgresql-og.png', 'supabase.com'),
('https://t3.gg/blog/posts/types-and-nextjs', 'An Inconsistent Truth: Next.js and Type Safety', '', 'const, query, inconsistent, nextjs, id, div, props, user, type, truth, return, function, types, safety', 'An Inconsistent Truth: Next.js and Type Safety December 2, 2021Imagine a world where Next.js was architected around type safety.\nimport type { NextApiRequest , NextApiResponse } from \"next\" ; import type { User } from \"@prisma/client\" ; export type UserRequestData = { user : User ; } ; export default async ( req : NextApiRequest , res : NextApiResponse < UserRequestData > ) => { const { userId } = req .\ndata ) return < div > Error: user not found </ div > ; return < div > Hello { data .\ndata ) return < div > Error: user not found </ div > ; return < div > Hello { data .\nfindFirst ( { where : { id : id } } ) ; return { props : { user } } ; } import Props from \"./_props\" ; export default function UserInfo ( props : Props ) { return < div > Hello { props .', '2021-12-03', 'https://t3.gg/images/next-typesafety/twitter.png', 't3.gg'),
('https://tanayagrawal.substack.com/p/linkedin-referrals', 'The art of finding referrals and landing job interviews on LinkedIn', 'Tanay Agrawal', 'send, person, message, job, networking, interviews, interested, referrals, landing, respond, art, connection, finding, linkedin', 'Are you looking for a job in the United States/Silicon Valley and not landing interviews even after 100s of applications?\nWith the importance of referrals being established, the next question to answer is: How do I actually get a referral?\nIn this blog article, I am going to lay down the process of finding connections and referrals on LinkedIn and make it easy and replicable.\nDuring that time, I added over 1000 connections which lead to ~50 networking conversations and 9 job interviews.\n#3 Personalize the messageDo not send connection requests without slightly personalizing the message.', '2021-12-03', 'https://cdn.substack.com/image/fetch/w_1200,c_limit,f_jpg,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7503f5c2-97d0-4ae2-871f-0e65636a76fe_480x480.gif', 'tanayagrawal.substack.com'),
('https://taras.glek.net/post/optimized-zip-format/', 'Firefox\'s Optimized Zip Format: Reading Zip Files Really Quickly', 'Taras Glek', 'central, optimized, really, format, files, firefox, read, zip, directory, quickly, readahead, reading, file, bytes, firefoxs', 'This post is about minimizing amount of disk IO and CPU overhead when reading Zip files.\nSome googling showed me that over past 11 years people have noticed that Firefox uses optimized zip files.\nTo extract a file from zip file one must:Scan backwards through zip file for End of Central Directory marker.\nZip file now looks like: | 4 bytes | Central Directory | Hot Files | Cold Files | End Of Central Directory Marker |.\nThus we have a sequentual-read-friendly zip file that can still be ready by zip tools that follow the spec.', '2021-12-03', 'https://www.codeproject.com/KB/cs/remotezip/diagram1.png', 'taras.glek.net'),
('https://tbz533.blogspot.com/2021/01/spin-your-own-autodiff-in-c.html', 'tbz533: Spin your own autodiff in C++', '', 'sample, c, distributions, user, jags, spin, ones, l, tbz533, autodiff, socalled, models, trick, standard', 'The so-called \"ones trick\" for JAGS and BUGS models allows the user to sample from distributions that are not in the standard l...', '2021-12-03', 'https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-EbVd9yewaWU/X_I0oyjDfWI/AAAAAAAADCY/RwqR6eShn6cyW0u1ecY3D1DMpJNKCGcowCLcBGAsYHQ/w1200-h630-p-k-no-nu/ad_example1.png', 'tbz533.blogspot.com'),
('https://tech.marksblogg.com/fastest-fizz-buzz.html', 'The Fastest FizzBuzz Implementation', 'Mark Litwintschik', 'x, fizzbuzz, taskset, fastest, following, pv, cpu, code, implementation, output, fizz, run', 'In this post, I\'ll examine some of the optimisations found in the fastest FizzBuzz implementation to date.\n$ ./fizzbuzz | pv > /dev/null $ ./fizzbuzz | cat $ ./fizzbuzz | head This program may produce incorrect output if piped into two commands if the middle command uses the splice system call.\nThe following will run fizzbuzz on core 1 and run pv on core 2.\n$ taskset 1 ./fizzbuzz | taskset 2 pv > /dev/null The following will run pv on core 4 and it should run considerably slower than the above.\n$ taskset 1 ./fizzbuzz | taskset 4 pv > /dev/null The above optimisation lead to a 1.25x speed up during Omer\'s benchmark.', '2021-12-03', 'https://tech.marksblogg.com/theme/images/mark.jpg', 'tech.marksblogg.com'),
('https://techcrunch.com/2021/12/01/better-com-lays-off-9-of-its-staff/', 'Ahead of public market debut, Better.com lays off 9% of its staff – TechCrunch', '', 'lays, market, layoffs, ahead, speech, ryan, company, techcrunch, set, sheet, sources, billion, public, better, bettercom, debut, staff', 'One day after announcing an amendment to its SPAC agreement, digital mortgage lender Better.com confirmed today that it is laying off roughly 9% of its nearly 10,000 person staff.\nFor one, the mortgage market is expected to contract pretty significantly after 18 months of rapid expansion driven by historically lower interest rates.\nBottom line, the company has “too many people in the wrong places,” according to our sources, who preferred to remain anonymous.\nBetter’s automation efforts means fewer manual process and a business that is more machine-driven, hence the need for fewer human resources.\nOn Nov. 30, TechCrunch reported that the company was getting a cash infusion from its backers sooner than expected.', '2021-12-01', 'https://techcrunch.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/down-3765608_1280.jpg?w=675', 'techcrunch.com'),
('https://tedium.co/2019/06/20/geoworks-geos-history/', 'GeoWorks: The Other Windows', '', 'early, windows, really, operating, used, software, system, motif, interface, geoworks', 'The operating system eventually moved to the PC in the early ’90s in a more advanced form, and Berkeley Softworks changed its name to GeoWorks.\nOverall, these offerings were great for home users, an audience that Microsoft hadn’t really emphasized early on in Windows’ history.\nWindows 3.1 really needed a 486 to shine, but GeoWorks could effectively run on a 286 or 386 without any problem.\n“Estimates of the total number of XTs and 286s that can’t do Windows right (Windows 3.0 was designed primarily for 80386-based computers) range as high as 20 million,” a 1991 Compute!\nEven GeoWorks’ biggest fans knew it didn’t stand a chance against Windows, due to Microsoft’s already-established goodwill.', '2019-06-20', 'https://images.tedium.co/2018/01/exkz5jdbejhaorz9nfaz--1-.gif', 'tedium.co'),
('https://tedium.co/2021/12/01/jingpad-a1-linux-tablet-review/', 'JingPad Review: A Linux Tablet With Potential, But Rough Edges', '', 'tablet, edges, linux, device, things, potential, android, interface, jingos, hardware, keyboard, review, rough, lot, jingpad', 'So it makes sense that there have been some fascinating efforts to reinvent the Linux ecosystem around hardware.\nToday’s Tedium takes an up-close look at the JingPad A1, an experimental new tablet worth looking into.\nMeet the JingPad: The hardware is really good … with some notable capability gaps The JingPad, on the surface, puts on a good show.\n(That’s right, this 2021 Linux device is rocking a four-year-old version of the Linux kernel.)\nThat, to me, suggests that hardware acceleration is available in the Android interface, but not to the Linux interface itself.', '2021-12-01', 'https://images.tedium.co/uploads/tedium120121.gif', 'tedium.co'),
('https://text.npr.org/1060600043', 'Twitter photo-removal policy aimed at improving privacy sparks concerns over misuse', '', 'improving, videos, privacy, media, images, concerns, private, twitter, users, sparks, policy, aimed, public, misuse, information, photoremoval', '\"The misuse of private media can affect everyone, but can have a disproportionate effect on women, activists, dissidents, and members of minority communities.\"\nPublic figures are exempt from the policy, Twitter said.\nCritics say the policy lets Twitter decide what\'s newsworthyTwitter said that media showing people participating in public events, including large-scale protests and sports games, are generally allowed under the policy.\nMeta, Facebook\'s parent company, said it planned to end its facial recognition system last month over privacy concerns.\n\"It will certainly give moderators an extra set of options when dealing with cases of third parties using the private information (such as physical address, legal name, etc.)', '2021-12-03', 'data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAABAAAAAQCAYAAAAf8/9hAAAAAXNSR0IArs4c6QAAAHlJREFUOBFjYBgFFIcA48cYpf/opvAv+YouxODXshZDbFONDSMLSJRv8V245KdYZTD7//8XcDFGRgkwe2O1NVzMv/UomA02AMQCaUQ2CCQG0ohsEEgMphHEBgEmCIWdRNeMTRXYBTBnw2iYQpjTYXx022Hio/RAhwAAjXEfJrIXnj4AAAAASUVORK5CYII=', 'text.npr.org'),
('https://theconvivialsociety.substack.com/p/you-cant-optimize-for-rest', 'You Can\'t Optimize For Rest', 'L. M. Sacasas', 'sleep, exhaustion, man, ellul, optimize, cant, system, work, technique, society, human, rest', 'In this installment I write a bit about burnout, exhaustion, and rest.\nAs it turned out, that article on the different forms of rest takes a recent book as its point of departure.\nOthers have written about this phenomenon perceptively and eloquently, particularly if we consider discussions of rest, exhaustion, and burnout together with similar discussions about the changing nature and meaning of work.\nThese days I find it helpful to gloss what technique meant for Ellul as the tyrannical imperative to optimize everything.\nRest takes on the character of a project to be completed or an experience to be consumed.', '2021-12-03', 'https://cdn.substack.com/image/fetch/w_1200,c_limit,f_jpg,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F074c6296-3c12-4a3c-9097-567ac92907be_256x256.png', 'theconvivialsociety.substack.com'),
('https://themarkup.org/prediction-bias/2021/12/02/crime-prediction-software-promised-to-be-free-of-biases-new-data-shows-it-perpetuates-them', 'Crime Prediction Software Promised to Be Free of Biases. New Data Shows It Perpetuates Them – The Markup', 'Aaron Sankin, Dhruv Mehrotra, Surya Mattu, Annie Gilbertson, Investigative Reporter, Senior Data Engineer, Investigative Data Journalist, Dell Cameron, Josh Lash, Daniel Lempres', 'latino, perpetuates, free, crime, shows, neighborhoods, predpol, crimes, promised, biases, predictions, software, black, prediction, data, markup', 'He instead offered to allow us to use the software for free on publicly available crime data instead of reporting on the data we had gathered.\nThe study authors developed a potential tweak to the algorithm that they said resulted in a more even distribution of crime predictions.\nSource: U.S. Department of Justice Bureau of Justice Statistics“We use crime data as reported to the police by the victims themselves,” he said.\nCrime prediction algorithms use this historical crime report data to forecast where crime will occur.\nCocoa, Fla., shows the greatest difference between highest and lowest prediction neighborhoods, Orange County, Fla., the lowest.', '2021-12-02', 'https://mrkp-static-production.themarkup.org/uploads/2021/11/predpol_homepage_police_crop-1200x628.jpg', 'themarkup.org');
