('https://theprint.in/india/how-father-son-duo-helped-techies-hack-exams-earn-top-scores-for-big-payday/774001/', 'How father-son duo helped techies ‘hack exams’, earn top scores for big payday', 'Bismee Taskin', 'certifications, earn, exams, online, delhi, various, helped, certification, big, payday, score, techies, dcp, scores, hack, fatherson, software, source, duo', 'The trio apparently specialised in cracking various online tech certification exams.\nHe added that high scores in these competitive exams can make a big difference to the career progress of IT aspirants.\nThe modus operandiAccording to the police, Deep and his father Rajesh gave potential clients a “100 per cent guarantee” of passing online certification exams.\nHe added that for actually attempting these exams, the father-son pair hired Alam who “hacked sites for various exams — WS (Amazon Web Services), Azure, CompTIA A+, PMP, CISM, CEH (Cyber Ethical Hacking), etc by getting remote access through apps”.\nThe exams which were earlier organised offline, are now being conducted online through various software.', '2021-11-30', 'https://static.theprint.in/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/IT-scamsters.jpg', 'theprint.in'),
('https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/india-will-have-nine-nuclear-reactors-by-2024-govt/articleshow/88055446.cms', 'India will have nine nuclear reactors by 2024: Govt', 'Pti', 'unit, crore, covid, 2024, india, nuclear, plant, budget, reactors, govt, minister, energy, rs, units', 'The Kudankulam nuclear plant n Tamil Nadu (file photo)NEW DELHI: The nation will have nine nuclear reactors by 2024 and a new nuclear project, the first in northern India, will come up 150 kms away from Delhi in Gorakhpur of Haryana, the government informed the Rajya Sabha.\nThe minister said that nuclear energy will soon emerge as one of the most important sources of alternative or clean energy for the increasing power demand of the country.\nOn the expansion of Kudankulan nuclear plant, the Minister also said that \"hopefully in 2021, we plan to start the construction of unit 5 and unit 6 as well.\"\nDuring Covid itself we have increased the power generation by more than 4000 mega units in nuclear plans, he said.\nFor next 10 years also, there is a plan to increase the budget by Rs 10,000 crore per year, he said.', '2021-12-03', 'https://static.toiimg.com/thumb/msid-88055504,width-1070,height-580,imgsize-1492503,resizemode-75,overlay-toi_sw,pt-32,y_pad-40/photo.jpg', 'timesofindia.indiatimes.com'),
('https://tnc.news/2021/08/23/a-map-of-every-church-burnt-or-vandalized-since-the-residential-school-announcements/', 'UPDATE: A map of the 68 churches that have been vandalized or burned since the residential schools announcement', 'Journalist, Senior Research Fellow', 'parish, schools, st, churches, 68, update, building, map, bcst, calgary, investigating, nations, burned, church, residential, announcement, catholic, mission, vandalized', 'Sacred Heart Mission Church, Penticton, BC.,Sacred Heart Mission Church was burnt down on Monday, June 28.\nHouse Of Prayer Alliance Church, Calgary AB.,Investigators with the arson unit are looking into a fire that broke out on July 4 at a local Calgary church.\nSiksika First Nation Catholic Church, Siksika, AB.,On June 28, RCMP and fire officials responded to a fire at Siksika First Nation Catholic Church.\nOur Lady of Mercy Catholic Church, Kehewin, AB.,Our Lady of Mercy Catholic Church was completely destroyed following a fire that was deliberately set on Friday, July 9.\nPolish Roman Catholic Church, Saskatoon, SK.,A former Polish Roman Catholic Church located on private property near Redberry Lake was burnt to the ground on July 8.', '2021-08-23', 'https://static.tnc.news/media/2021/07/website-churchmap.jpg', 'tnc.news'),
('https://torrentfreak.com/google-removes-pirate-bay-domains-from-search-results-citing-dutch-court-order-211130/', 'Google Removes Pirate Bay Domains from Search Results Citing Dutch Court Order * TorrentFreak', '', 'domains, search, dutch, order, brein, sites, torrentfreak, google, results, court, isps, pirate, removes, antipiracy', 'Google has removed The Pirate Bay and more than 100 related domains from its search results in the Netherlands.\nAmong other things, Google actively demotes known pirate sites in its search results.\nGoogle Removes Pirate Bay DomainWith these earlier comments in mind, it’s surprising to see that Google has removed all search results for Pirate Bay’s main domain name for users with a Dutch IP address.\nThe Dutch results stand in stark contrast to those elsewhere in the world, where the same query returns tens of thousands of URLs.\nWhen the court requires ISPs to block these sites, Google may choose to follow suit again.', '2021-12-03', 'https://torrentfreak.com/apple-touch-icon.png', 'torrentfreak.com'),
