('https://win-vector.com/2021/12/02/composing-queries-in-the-data-algebra/', 'Composing Queries in the Data Algebra', 'John Mount', 'table, example, algebra, direct, working, tables, queries, set, data, sql, rows, composing, python', 'When working with multiple data tables we often need to know how for a given set of keys, how many instances of rows each table has.\nI would like to use such an example in Python as yet another introduction to the data algebra (an alternative to direct Pandas or direct SQL notation).\nFirst let’s import our packages and set up our example data.', '2021-12-02', 'https://i1.wp.com/win-vector.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/cropped-wvlogosmall.png?fit=512%2C512&ssl=1', 'win-vector.com'),
('https://wordy.pages.dev/', 'You don\'t need a NoSQL database', '', 'app, nosql, databases, database, fauna, need, dont, data, serverless, query, sql', 'You don\'t need a NoSQL databaseWhen I research a technology stack for a new project, I often find myself trying out various NoSQL databases.\nThe problem, though, is that for most apps, the tradeoffs you make by using a NoSQL database are just too big.\nLet\'s look at some of the common arguments in favor of NoSQL:\"Our new NoSQL database doesn\'t enforce a certain schema on you.\nPeople starting their app project with a NoSQL database tend to think, \"well, this app has fairly simple data needs, so we don\'t need advanced querying\".\nNoSQL databases are certainly the right tool for some jobs, but the most popular NoSQL databases receive an extraordinary amount of attention considering they\'re only truly applicable for a small amount of use cases.', '2021-12-03', '', 'wordy.pages.dev'),
('https://wwvarc.org/wwvmodannouncement', 'NIST announces upcoming modulation experiment start', '', 'signal, wwvh, hamsci, upcoming, test, radio, experiment, wwv, science, nist, citizen, hour, minute, start, announces, modulation', 'last updated November 4, 2021NIST, the National Institute of Science and Technology, is currently announcing an upcoming broadcast of a special test modulation signal to help with ionospheric research coordinated by HamSCI, the Ham Radio Science Citizen Investigation.\nThe WWV and WWVH on-air announcement reads:Beginning November 15, 2021, NIST will be broadcasting a test signal on minute 8 of each hour on WWV, and minute 48 on WWVH.\nThis signal has been created to assist in ionospheric research and is a joint effort of the Ham Radio Citizen Science Investigation (Ham Radio Science Citizen Investigation or HamSCI) and NIST.\nNIST is participating in a new project to study the ionosphere and its effects on high frequency (HF) radio propagation.\nThe signals will be sent at 8 minutes past each hour on WWV, and 48 minutes past each hour on WWVH.', '2021-12-03', 'https://wwvarc.org/sites/default/files/WW0WWV.logo_2_0.png', 'wwvarc.org'),
('https://www.afar.com/magazine/a-hotel-housekeeper-on-her-life-and-work', 'Queen of Clean', '', 'manager, rooms, room, children, queen, day, working, guest, hotel, clean, soho, vida', 'Since she first started working in the hospitality industry two decades ago, Vida Afram has cleaned nearly 60,000 hotel rooms.\nSome people treat the room like it’s their own house, separating dirty clothes from the clean clothes.\nSometimes guests will smile to her face, then complain to the hotel manager that their room wasn’t clean enough.\nSometimes the guests stay in the room, working, while she cleans.\nVida has been cleaning rooms at the Sixty SoHo Hotel for the past two decades.', '2021-12-03', 'https://afar-production.imgix.net/uploads/images/afar_post_headers/images/yu6wdPlUsB/original_Vida_49-Edit_20(1).jpg?crop=top&fit=crop&w=600&h=330', 'www.afar.com'),
('https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-59418123', 'Covid: Trigger of rare blood clots with AstraZeneca jab found by scientists', '', 'liver, thrombosis, commonly, trigger, astrazeneca, questions, rare, jab, blood, unanswered, susceptible, including, clots, veins, covid, research, remain, scientists', 'He added: \"Many questions still remain unanswered, including whether some people may be more susceptible than others and why the thrombosis (clotting) is most commonly in the veins of the brain and liver, but this may come with time and further research.\"', '2021-12-03', 'https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/1024/branded_news/3C2A/production/_121920451_mediaitem121920450.jpg', 'www.bbc.co.uk'),
('https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/technology-59400762', 'Huge fines and a ban on default passwords in new UK law', '', 'ongoing, default, passwords, day, overseen, force, turnover, regime, huge, global, uk, ban, law, fine, power, regulator, fines', 'The new regime will be overseen by a regulator, which will be appointed once the bill comes into force.\nIt will have the power to fine companies up to £10m or 4% of their global turnover, as well as up to £20,000 a day for ongoing contraventions.', '2021-12-03', 'https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/1024/branded_news/4D60/production/_121780891_dishwasher.png', 'www.bbc.co.uk'),
('https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-wales-59491185', 'Asbestos exposure from 20 years ago killed IT worker', '', 'meant, fair, ago, really, killed, know, couldnt, asbestos, 20, pronounce, son, google, exposure, worker, didnt, turned', '\"We couldn\'t even pronounce it.\nWe didn\'t even know what it meant.\nAnd to be fair, the consultant didn\'t know.\nBecause he turned to my son and he said, \'If you want to really know all about it, Google it.\'\"', '2021-12-03', 'https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/1024/branded_news/99B8/production/_121925393_jasonwilliamswhosadlypassedawayagedjust45withmesothelioma2.jpg', 'www.bbc.co.uk'),
('https://www.bearer.com/blog/why-hotwire', 'Why Hotwire in 2021', '', 'turbo, using, stack, html, 2021, streams, product, rails, page, hotwire, stimulus', 'The main technology behind Hotwire is Turbo, which is a variety of techniques to handle these HTML responses.\nTurbo streams for reducing custom JavaScriptUsing Turbo streams allowed us to greatly reduce JS usage for common UI behaviors, like modal popups, adding and removing items from a list, and responsively disclosing form elements.\nWe’re also using streams to keep the application state on the server, and then enforcing any updates on the client.\nHotwire consThe primary con is that Hotwire is still, relatively, new.\nTo help with that, we have some new Rails and Hotwire articles in the pipeline so keep an eye out for them.', '2021-12-03', 'https://assets.website-files.com/61570a290fb0e042e260602f/61a7f8ce0d90fa8e6cf3c456_Bearer%20blog%20Twitter%20example-2.png', 'www.bearer.com'),
('https://www.betrfs.org/', 'BetrFS', '', 'writes, structure, small, upper, ε, system, bε, file, tree, trees, betrfs', 'The Bε-tree File System, or BetrFS, is an in-kernel file system that uses Bε trees to organize on-disk storage.\nBε trees are a write-optimized dictionary, and offer the same asymptotic behavior for sequential I/O and point queries as a B-tree.\nThe goal of BetrFS is to realize performance that strictly dominates the performance of current, general-purpose file systems.\nWrite-Optimized Dictionaries include Bε trees, Log-Structured Merge Trees (LSM Trees), and COLAs.\nBetrFS is an in-kernel file system, based on the opensource fractal tree implementation from Tokutek Inc. A fractal tree is a specialized variant of a B ε tree.', '2021-12-03', '', 'www.betrfs.org'),
('https://www.blogto.com/tech/2021/12/right-to-disconnect-ontario/', 'It\'s now officially illegal in Ontario for your boss to bug you at home after-hours', '', 'bug, mcnaughton, workers, help, boss, insurance, act, working, illegal, workplace, work, spend, employees, afterhours, officially, ontario', 'Ontario just passed a law making it illegal for bosses to bug their employees after-hours.\nThe provincial government passed the Working for Workers Act, 2021, which was first proposed in October.\nLockdowns have many people working from home, which while popular, tends to blur the line between work time and personal time.\nOntario wants to keep labour laws at \"pace with the acceleration of new technology, automation, and remote work,\" Monte McNaughton, Minister of Labour, Training and Skills Development said.\nAllow surpluses in the Workplace Safety and Insurance Board’s Insurance Fund to be distributed over certain levels to businesses, helping them cope with the impacts of COVID-19.', '2021-12-03', 'https://media.blogto.com/articles/2021121-right-to-disconnect-44.jpg?w=1200&cmd=resize_then_crop&height=630&quality=70', 'www.blogto.com'),
('https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2021-12-02/goldman-executives-want-to-get-paid', 'Are you a robot?', '', 'terms, loading, javascript, supports, robot, review, policy, happenplease, service, sure, information', 'Why did this happen?\nPlease make sure your browser supports JavaScript and cookies and that you are not blocking them from loading.\nFor more information you can review our Terms of Service and Cookie Policy.', '2021-12-02', '', 'www.bloomberg.com'),
('https://www.bosch-presse.de/pressportal/de/en/longer-range-as-standard-bosch-gives-go-ahead-for-volume-production-of-silicon-carbide-chips-235722.html', 'Longer range as standard: Bosch gives go-ahead for volume production of silicon carbide chips', '', 'chips, sic, silicon, support, innovative, production, carbide, volume, goahead, future, range, bosch, gives, semiconductors, development, longer, standard', 'After several years of development, Bosch is now starting volume production of power semiconductors made of this innovative material, supplying automotive manufacturers worldwide.\nWe want to become a global leader in the production of SiC chips for electromobility,” says Harald Kroeger, member of the board of management of Robert Bosch GmbH.\nTwo years ago, the supplier of technology and services had announced that it would push ahead with the development of SiC chips and enter production.\nIn the future, Bosch intends to expand its production capacity for SiC power semiconductors to a unit volume running into the hundreds of millions.\nIn parallel, work is also being done on the second generation of SiC chips, which will be even more efficient and should be ready for volume production as of 2022.', '2021-12-03', 'https://www.bosch-presse.de/pressportal/de/media/dam_images/pi11408/bosch_sic_wafer_2-standard_1280x720_img_w1280.png', 'www.bosch-presse.de'),
('https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/jasonleopold/cia-employees-sex-crimes-children-secret-files-foia', 'CIA Files Say Staffers Committed Sex Crimes Involving Children. They Weren’t Prosecuted.', 'Jason Leopold, Buzzfeed News Reporter, Anthony Cormier', 'cia, werent, involving, abuse, inspector, security, committed, prosecuted, images, files, crimes, employee, say, general, agency, sexual, sex, child, staffers', 'The documents also reveal the pattern of sexual abuse cases, whereby internal investigators unearthed evidence of sexual crimes involving children but federal prosecutors brought no charges.\nOf the 10 workers who the inspector general found had committed sexual crimes involving children, five were fired or resigned.\nHe later pleaded guilty to the child abuse charges and registered as a sex offender.\nSchulte faces a separate trial on the child sexual abuse charges.\n●Read the CIA inspector general reports on child abuse', '2021-12-03', 'https://img.buzzfeed.com/buzzfeed-static/static/2021-12/1/19/asset/c2c13933c826/sub-buzz-3719-1638385887-5.jpg?crop=1600:838;0,78', 'www.buzzfeednews.com'),
('https://www.capellaspace.com/gallery/', 'Gallery Archive', '', 'training, variety, sar, best, visibility, wake, archive, tool, data, synthetic, open, gallery', 'Synthetic Aperture Radar (SAR) satellite data is a critical tool for making decision.\nWhether you are gaining rapid visibility in the wake of a natural disaster or training the next generation of machine learning algorithms, you need the best quality data to drive the best possible outcomes.\nExplore our SAR Image Gallery to see how SAR has helped government and commercial customers across a variety of applications.\nAll data are available to all approved open data program members.\nWould you like to download all of our Open Data?', '2021-12-03', 'https://www.capellaspace.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/cropped-favicon-32x32.png', 'www.capellaspace.com'),
('https://www.cnbc.com/2021/12/02/ftc-sues-to-block-nvidias-40-billion-acquisition-of-arm.html', 'FTC sues to block Nvidia\'s $40 billion acquisition of Arm', 'Lauren Feiner Kif Leswing, Lauren Feiner, Kif Leswing', 'technology, block, processors, deal, reduced, proposed, supplier, ftc, 40, sues, acquisition, nvidia, architecture, billion, arm, nvidias', 'Patrick T. Fallon | Bloomberg | Getty ImagesThe Federal Trade Commission on Thursday sued to block Nvidia\'s $40 billion acquisition of Arm from SoftBank on antitrust grounds.\nThe U.S. action is the biggest hurdle it has faced yet, and threatens whether the deal will be completed.\nArm is a core supplier of architecture technology to most semiconductor companies.\nBut the company\'s role in the chip industry was historically as a neutral supplier, raising concerns that Nvidia could cut off competitors from essential Arm technology.\nSome of Nvidia\'s processors also use Arm-designed cores and its Arm architecture, although the company is best known for graphics processors, which use different architecture.', '2021-12-02', 'https://image.cnbcfm.com/api/v1/image/106390082-1581623646542gettyimages-1177538076.jpeg?v=1581623682', 'www.cnbc.com'),
('https://www.cnn.com/2021/12/02/europe/germany-lockdown-covid-restrictions-intl/index.html', 'Germany locks down unvaccinated people, as leaders plan to make shots compulsory', 'Nadine Schmidt, Frederik Pleitgen', 'scholz, olaf, leaders, germany, compulsory, restrictions, locks, unvaccinated, shots, vaccinations, tightened, merkel, mandatory, plan', 'Berlin (CNN) Germany on Thursday announced a nationwide lockdown for the unvaccinated, as its leaders backed plans for mandatory vaccinations in the coming months.\nThe pair also backed proposals for mandatory vaccinations, which if voted through the parliament could take effect from February at the earliest.\nUnder the tightened restrictions, unvaccinated people can only meet two people from another household.\nBars and nightclubs must shut down in areas with an incidence rate above 350 cases per 100,000 people over one week.\nActing Chancellor Angela Merkel and Olaf Scholz hold a press conference on tightened Covid-19 restrictions Thursday.', '2021-12-02', 'https://cdn.cnn.com/cnnnext/dam/assets/211202091825-01-merkel-scholz-covid-presser-1202-super-tease.jpg', 'www.cnn.com'),
('https://www.earth.li/~noodles/blog/2021/12/desktop-work-life-balance.html', 'Building a desktop to improve my work/life balance', '', 'improve, switch, worklife, desktop, working, things, building, work, monitor, personal, need, setup, balance, laptop, ive', 'I set my work laptop on the stand on a Monday morning and it sits there until Friday evening, when it gets switched for the personal laptop.\nThis turns out to be perfect; I’ve no need for a PCIe slot or anything more than an m.2 SSD.\nAlso from the point of view I don’t need to setup the personal config, I can pick up where I left off.\nIt’s also got me thinking about other minor improvements I should make to my home working environment to try and improve things.\nLots of cheap options I’m not convinced about, and I’ve had a few ridiculously priced options from photographer friends; suggestions welcome.', '2021-12-03', 'https://www.earth.li/~noodles/blog/images/2021/deskmini.jpg', 'www.earth.li'),
('https://www.easypost.com/careers', 'Careers at EasyPost', '', 'waste, sameday, shipments, offer, easypost, removed, week, questions, careers, shippinghow, technology, shipping', 'The future of shippingHow can modern, flexible technology improve the customer experience of shipping?\nWhat if every business was able to offer same-day shipping?\nHow much waste would be removed from the environment if all our shipments were consolidated into one delivery per week?\nAt EasyPost, we\'re figuring out the answer to these questions and more.', '2021-12-03', 'https://assets.easypost.com/assets/images/branding/easypost-primary-icon-padded.69db27030b30ab917e891bfed0983781.png', 'www.easypost.com'),
('https://www.economist.com/finance-and-economics/2021/12/04/the-explosion-in-stablecoins-revives-a-debate-around-free-banking', 'The explosion in stablecoins revives a debate around “free banking”', 'The Economist', 'free, tokens, banks, tether, regulation, debate, money, stablecoins, currency, revives, issued, notes, explosion, banking', 'Indeed, recent discussions about stablecoins have sparked a lively debate around the history of privately issued money.\nBefore America instituted a national currency in 1863, banks issued their own banknotes, backed by assets and redeemable for gold or silver.\nCritics of stablecoins often point to this period of free banking, and the example of unstable “wildcat” banks in particular, as a cautionary tale.\nNor is it clear that wildcat banks are the summation of all historical experience of privately issued money.\nThree large banks and several smaller lenders all issued currency and redeemed each other’s notes at their full value.', '2021-12-04', 'https://www.economist.com/img/b/1280/720/90/sites/default/files/images/print-edition/20211204_FND000_0.jpg', 'www.economist.com'),
('https://www.eff.org/deeplinks/2021/10/why-it-so-hard-figure-out-what-do-when-you-lose-your-account', 'Why Is It So Hard to Figure Out What to Do When You Lose Your Account?', 'Katharine Trendacosta', 'lose, figure, hard, rules, infringer, twitter, company, users, content, repeat, policies, policy, account', 'And it’s even worse when you can’t figure out why your account was closed, much less how to get it restored.\nOver the summer, writer and meme king Chuck Tingle found his Twitter account suspended due to running afoul of Twitter’s ill-defined repeat infringer policy.\nUnder appropriate circumstances we may suspend user accounts under our repeat infringer policy.\nHowever, we may take retractions and counter-notices into account when applying our repeat infringer policy.\nWhen Tingle lost his account under its repeat infringer policy, he found that because his account was suspended, he couldn’t use Twitter’s forms to contest the takedowns.', '2021-10-21', 'https://www.eff.org/files/banner_library/tossed-2_0.jpg', 'www.eff.org'),
('https://www.eurekalert.org/news-releases/936266', 'Cannabis impacts sperm counts, motility in two generations of mice', '', 'motility, male, study, impacts, exposed, generations, sperm, cannabis, mice, counts, exposure, reproductive', 'PULLMAN, Wash. – An intense but short-term exposure to cannabis vapor lowered sperm counts and slowed sperm movement, or motility, not only in the directly exposed male mice but also in their sons.\nHuman sperm counts have declined by as much as 59% in recent decades, according to some estimates.\nThe researchers then compared sperm counts and motility in those mice to the unexposed control group.\nThey found that immediately after the exposure period, the mice’s sperm motility decreased, and after one month, sperm counts were lower.\nA third-generation, the grandsons of the exposed male mice, did not show the same impacts, however, which suggests that the cannabis exposure impacted the second-generation mice at a developmental stage.', '2021-12-03', 'https://www.eurekalert.org/images/EurekAlert-bluebg_Twitter_601X601.png', 'www.eurekalert.org'),
('https://www.filfre.net/2021/11/boffo-games/', '» Boffo Games The Digital Antiquarian', 'Jimmy Maher, Owen C, Josh Martin, David Meyer-Lindenberg, Marcus Johnson', 'antiquarian, media, steve, games, bar, space, game, meretzky, infocom, digital, boffo, dornbrook', 'Unlike Dornbrook, Meretzky had stayed in the games industry since Infocom’s shuttering, designing four adventures for Legend Entertainment and one for Activision from his Boston home.\nAnd so Boffo Games was born.\nAfter Hodj ‘n’ Podj, the story of Boffo turns into a numbing parade of games that almost were.\nIf The Space Bar sold ten copies, that was ten too many; I hope those ten buyers returned it for a refund.\nI tend to see Meretzky’s rather disappointing output during the 1990s — including not only his Boffo games but those he did for Legend and Activision — as another ironic testament to Infocom’s genius for process.', '2021-12-03', 'https://www.filfre.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/s-l1600.jpg', 'www.filfre.net'),
('https://www.firstthings.com/web-exclusives/2021/11/the-joys-of-the-harpsichord', 'The Joys of the Harpsichord | John Ahern', '', 'hall, musical, joys, communication, instrument, variations, concert, piano, sound, music, ahern, harpsichord, john', 'But as I later learned, the sound of an actual harpsichord is nothing like that.\nWhen I sight-read the Goldberg Variations at my harpsichord, I am receiving a communication from Bach and joining a conversation.\nFor most people, music is now no longer a discursive activity, but an “experience.”The piano excels in the concert hall.\nAnd of course, in such a context, if the piano were pitted against the harpsichord, the piano undoubtedly would win.\nBut the piano concert is an experience, not a discourse.', '2021-11-22', 'https://d2ipgh48lxx565.cloudfront.net/uploads/article_618ed7f4b24ba.jpeg?Expires=1640185988&Signature=W~pQvIGN9jVAjXLJNUBcU-K9B2BT9hqqhdsuyYrkm0ery~JUv~CTk1uuB3jxLMGvXojn4xLojupKa71e~AS2MoIzy2pT1qegXB04MnNcnl2qbak67wnakQrfMhJ4D11D3M8eLbn3ngJeS006wwOCRrssKzri6iW~Tq9fZaYg9kFbLWfkBL--cC6pPFyBktbyrvM6uDh05MWoxNtXGGGQT1G5KcK1EG97aLcCVb9Kza~RPpSqkDhL6~0VPjG7rI6462qMZUI2GPKpd04Y2icfIf7Md8LJcDmhbEHBAqtDstVsf4GLsESGAS8XDNH0ncYcpG6nKgfYI6zyUP946yHLTA__&Key-Pair-Id=APKAIN7SVXNLPAOVDKZQ', 'www.firstthings.com'),
('https://www.fisher-price.com/en-us/product/chatter-telephone-hgj69', 'Chatter Telephone', '', 'technology, chatter, dial, wireless, working, comes, telephone, wheels, mobile, phone', 'Introducing the special edition Fisher-Price® Chatter Telephone™ — a phone smart enough not to come with any apps.\nIts intuitive bulky face design comes with a \'super-advanced\' rotary dial and connects to your mobile device via Bluetooth® wireless technology, so you can make and receive real calls through your existing phone plan.\nThis working Chatter Telephone™ is so mobile, it even comes with wheels.\nPlus, it has grownup functionality like speakerphone and the ability to dial out.\nAvailable exclusively at Best Buy® while supplies last.', '2021-12-03', 'https://images.mattel.com/scene7/HGJ69_Viewer', 'www.fisher-price.com'),
('https://www.ftc.gov/news-events/press-releases/2021/12/ftc-sues-block-40-billion-semiconductor-chip-merger', 'FTC Sues to Block $40 Billion Semiconductor Chip Merger', '', 'computing, sues, competition, complaint, block, arm, merger, 40, nvidia, semiconductor, billion, markets, ftc, products, technology, chip, arms', 'The Federal Trade Commission today sued to block U.S. chip supplier Nvidia Corp.’s $40 billion acquisition of U.K. chip design provider Arm Ltd. Semiconductor chips power the computers and technologies that are essential to our modern economy and society.\n“The FTC is suing to block the largest semiconductor chip merger in history to prevent a chip conglomerate from stifling the innovation pipeline for next-generation technologies,” said FTC Bureau of Competition Director Holly Vedova.\n“Tomorrow’s technologies depend on preserving today’s competitive, cutting-edge chip markets.\nThis proposed deal would distort Arm’s incentives in chip markets and allow the combined firm to unfairly undermine Nvidia’s rivals.\nIn these areas, both Nvidia and important competitors to Nvidia rely on Arm’s technology to develop their own competing products.', '2021-12-02', 'https://www.ftc.gov/sites/default/files/images/press-releases/social-share/ftc_social_share_default_en_2.jpg', 'www.ftc.gov'),
('https://www.gandi.net/en-US/domain/tld/io', '.io domain names', '', 'io, maximum, registration, registered, names, price, order, strongly, renew, period, possibleif, longest, domain', 'As such, we will be carrying over this price increase to our own price grids.\nWe strongly encourage you to renew your domain(s) before December 31, 2021 in order to benefit from the current price for the longest registration period possible.\nIf your domain name is currently registered for 1 year, you may renew it for a maximum of 9 years.', '2021-12-03', 'https://www.gandi.net/static/images/gandi-favicon-192.9d8e7b4c4306.png', 'www.gandi.net'),
('https://www.garbageday.email/p/right-clickers-vs-the-monkey-jpg', 'Right-clickers vs. the monkey JPG owners', 'Ryan Broderick, Jamal Hinton, Debbie Mia, Jessica Ritchey', 'vs, internet, really, user, monkey, money, twitter, culture, actually, owners, jpg, furries, online, rightclickers, crypto', 'Last week, a Twitter user named @nicodotgay downloaded all 10,000 of the Lazy Lion NFTs and turned them into a mosaic of a right-click.\nThe best overall articulation I’ve seen so far of why Web3 is so hated by many online subcultures right now was from @nicodotgay, the Twitter user behind the right-click mosaic.\nPorn, forever looking for ways to bypass payment blocks from payment companies, famously willing to champion new technologies,” Twitter user freyjaerlings wrote recently.\nMake your own conclusions.”And Twitter user @outstarwalker tweeted screenshots of two tweets arguing similar points, which are embedded below.\nWhat I’m saying here is that this looming culture war — between the right-clickers and monkey JPG owners — is actually a waste of time.', '2021-12-03', 'https://cdn.substack.com/image/fetch/w_1200,c_limit,f_jpg,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fpbs.substack.com%2Fmedia%2FFD8GIhOXwAYbx_E.jpg', 'www.garbageday.email'),
('https://www.gpsworld.com/russia-issues-threat-to-gps-satellites/', 'Russia issues threat to GPS satellites - GPS World', 'Tracy Cozzens', 'asat, station, iss, space, russia, missiles, antisatellite, world, satellites, issues, threat, stability, gps, nations, debris', 'The Kremlin warned it could blow up 32 GPS satellites with its new anti-satellite technology, ASAT, which it tested Nov. 15 on a retired Soviet Tselina-D satellite, according to numerous news reports.\n“Due to the debris generated by the destructive Russian Anti-Satellite (ASAT) test, ISS astronauts and cosmonauts undertook emergency procedures for safety,” said NASA Administrator Bill Nelson.\n“Their actions are reckless and dangerous, threatening as well the Chinese space station and the taikonauts on board.\nAll nations have a responsibility to prevent the purposeful creation of space debris from ASATs and to foster a safe, sustainable space environment.\n“Russia’s tests of direct-ascent anti-satellite weapons clearly demonstrate that Russia continues to pursue counterspace weapon systems that undermine strategic stability and pose a threat to all nations.”', '2021-11-29', 'https://www.gpsworld.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/GettyImages-692925488-Russia-F.jpg', 'www.gpsworld.com'),
('https://www.gutenberg.org/about/background/50years.html', '50 years of eBooks: 1971-2021', '', 'ebooks, 50, free, printing, literature, works, michael, gutenberg, press, innovation, 19712021, project', '50 years of eBooks: 1971-2021July 4, 2021 – In 1997, Time-Life magazine picked the movable type printing press as the most important invention of the second millennium.\nLike most important innovations and social changes, the printing press was an evolution that had deep roots in history.\nBy the turn of the new millennium, Project Gutenberg was producing thousands of new eBooks per year.\nProject Gutenberg celebrates 50 years of eBooks, and of continuously improving methods for creating and distributing them.\nProject Gutenberg was built by volunteers, and all new eBooks are the result of volunteer effort.', '2021-12-03', 'https://www.gutenberg.org/gutenberg/pg-logo-144x144.png', 'www.gutenberg.org'),
('https://www.honeycomb.io/blog/scaling-kafka-observability-pipelines/', 'Scaling Kafka at Honeycomb', 'Liz Fong-Jones', 'kafka, honeycomb, hours, instances, cpu, scaling, confluent, graviton2, data, instance, storage, retriever', 'Kafka as a managed service also exists in the form of Amazon Managed Streaming for Apache Kafka (MSK), Confluent Cloud, and others.\nIn the words of our platform engineering manager, Ben Hartshorne, Kafka is the “beating heart” of Honeycomb, powering our 99.99% ingest availability SLO.\nWe were already stretching the limits of i3en.3xlarge on every dimension except the amount of SSD provided as instance storage.\nAfter all, we already terminate Kafka instances every week, just like we terminate retrievers, so we can continuously verify that our automation works and there is enough headroom to replace nodes.\nWe hope hearing how we managed our Kafka-based telemetry ingest pipeline is helpful to you in scaling your own Kafka clusters.', '2021-11-30', 'https://www.honeycomb.io/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/image8.1.png', 'www.honeycomb.io'),
('https://www.insider.com/codex-seraphinianus-luigi-serafini-interview-40th-anniversary-edition-2021-11', 'The weirdest book in the world just turned 40. We talked to its creator.', 'Chris Kaye', 'book, talked, really, codex, know, creator, maybe, weirdest, writing, serafini, luigi, world, dont, pages, drawing, 40, turned', 'They were my first fans,\" Luigi Serafini says from his studio in Rome, Italy.\n\"Their lives were writing pages,\" Serafini adds, \"They were fascinated by something which cannot be read, so that\'s really funny.\"\nWhen I write the Codex, I use the Codex writing, I feel absolutely harmonious.\nLuigi Serafini(c) Luigi Serafini / Courtesy of Rizzoli New YorkSerafini continues to work in mediums from sculpture to furniture design to architecture, theater scenery, and costumes.\nSo 40 years ago, it was page, I don\'t know, 300,\" he says.', '2021-11-23', 'https://i.insider.com/6192f7618e9bfa001987167f?width=1200&format=jpeg', 'www.insider.com'),
('https://www.jeffgeerling.com/blog/2021/turing-pi-2-4-raspberry-pi-nodes-on-mini-itx-board', 'Turing Pi 2: 4 Raspberry Pi nodes on a mini ITX board', '', 'board, running, hpl, mini, turing, raspberry, itx, pi, cluster, nodes, slot, node, power', 'So this year, I was excited when the folks at Turing Pi sent me a Turing Pi 2 to test drive.\nBut the folks at Turing Pi seem set on having all the features ironed out for a January 2022 launch.\nPowerIn a first for a Raspberry Pi board, the Turing Pi 2 gets its power via a standard ATX 24-pin power header.\nYou can use any standard PC PSU, or even a Pico PSU and 12V adapter to power the Turing Pi 2.\nIt should be available in January 2022, and hopefully in greater quantities than the Turing Pi 1, which was almost always out of stock!', '2021-12-03', 'https://www.jeffgeerling.com/apple-touch-icon.png', 'www.jeffgeerling.com'),
('https://www.jessesquires.com/blog/2021/12/01/my-worst-tech-interview-experience/', 'My worst tech interview experience', 'Jesse Squires', 'interview, team, experience, writing, thats, sort, interviewer, whiteboard, posts, tech, worst, swift, ive', 'Everyone in tech seems to have a “terrible tech interview” story.\nSurprisingly, a few members of the early Swift team ended up leaving Apple and joining Facebook to work on HHVM or something similar, not sure.\nAnother strange thing about this experience is that over the years, I’ve watched some of the people from my interview loop give talks at WWDC.\n* * *Since that experience, I’ve been on both sides of the interview process dozens and dozens of times at various companies.\nAnd my interview experience with that team was just that — a complete waste of my time and theirs.', '2021-12-01', 'https://www.jessesquires.com/img/logo.png', 'www.jessesquires.com'),
('https://www.jezuk.co.uk/tags/software-tools-in-c++.html', 'Tag: software-tools-in-c++', 'Jez Higgins, Jezuk Ltd', 'sense, good, programs, study, reliable, programming, significant, writing, easy, tag, softwaretoolsinc, seeing', 'Good Programming is not learned from generalities, but by seeing how significant programs can be made clean, easy to read, easy to maintain and modify, human-engineered, efficient, and reliable, by the application of common sense and good programming practices.\nCareful study and imitation of good programs leads to better writing.', '2021-12-03', 'https://www.jezuk.co.uk/files/illuminated-by-monitor-light.jpg', 'www.jezuk.co.uk'),
('https://www.justice.gov/usao-sdny/pr/former-employee-technology-company-charged-stealing-confidential-data-and-extorting', 'Former Employee Of Technology Company Charged With Stealing Confidential Data And Extorting Company For Ransom While Posing As Anonymous Attacker', '', 'technology, extorting, maximum, incident, access, posing, fbi, sharp, company, company1s, employee, company1, stealing, data, confidential, computer, charged, ransom', 'SHARP was a senior developer who had access to credentials for Company-1’s Amazon Web Services (“AWS”) and GitHub Inc. (“GitHub”) servers.\nIn about December 2020, SHARP repeatedly misused his administrative access to download gigabytes of confidential data from his employer.\nAt one point during the exfiltration of Company-1 data, SHARP’s home IP address became unmasked following a temporary internet outage at SHARP’s home.\nDuring the course of the Incident, SHARP caused damage to Company-1’s computer systems by altering log retention policies and other files, to conceal his unauthorized activity on the network.\nIn those stories, SHARP identified himself as an anonymous whistleblower within Company-1 who had worked on remediating the Incident.', '2021-12-01', 'https://www.justice.gov/sites/all/modules/features/doj_sharing/images/doj-seal-fb.jpg', 'www.justice.gov'),
('https://www.latimes.com/homeless-housing/story/2021-12-02/facing-housing-crisis-l-a-voters-back-duplexes-in-single-family-neighborhoods', 'Facing housing crisis, L.A. voters back duplexes in single-family neighborhoods', 'Staff Writer, Liam Dillon Covers The Issues Of Housing Affordability, Neighborhood Change Across California For The Los Angeles Times.', 'la, voters, neighborhoods, laws, singlefamily, crisis, sb, facing, los, duplexes, housing, poll, state, law, angeles', 'A majority of Los Angeles County voters back two new state laws designed to spur housing construction, including one that significantly changes traditional single-family zoning, a new poll finds.\nThe fight stirred intense opposition among homeowner groups, especially in Los Angeles, where opponents said the proposals threatened to destroy single-family neighborhoods.\nCountywide, 55% of voters support Senate Bill 9, which lets property owners construct duplexes, and in some cases fourplexes, in most single-family-home neighborhoods statewide.\nAlmost two-thirds of all the residences in the state are single-family homes and as much as three-quarters of the developable land in the state is now zoned only for single-family housing, according to a survey by UC Berkeley’s Terner Center for Housing Innovation.\nThe poll was conducted between Oct. 27 and Nov. 3 among 906 registered voters in L.A. County.', '2021-12-02', 'https://ca-times.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/3caa735/2147483647/strip/true/crop/3900x2048+0+277/resize/1200x630!/quality/90/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcalifornia-times-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2a%2F9f%2F670087a94fd591c8d9bd095c3b41%2Fla-photos-1staff-714018-et-backyard-homes-232.jpg', 'www.latimes.com');
INSERT INTO `articles` (`url`, `title`, `authors`, `tags`, `summary`, `publish_date`, `image_url`, `domain`) VALUES
('https://www.lrt.lt/en/news-in-english/19/1555667/chinese-ports-start-blocking-lithuanian-goods-media', 'Chinese ports start blocking Lithuanian goods – media', '', 'chinese, representation, foreign, media, ministry, goods, lithuanian, ports, customs, exporters, start, chinas, blocking, reported, china', 'Lithuanian exporters have reported they cannot clear their goods through Chinese customs after the country was apparently dropped from China\'s customs registry.\n15min.lt reported on Thursday that a Lithuanian company exporting wood to China was not allowed to unload in one of the country\'s ports.\nThe Lithuanian Foreign Ministry has also confirmed to BNS that Lithuanian exporters are facing issues in China.\nAccording to 15min.lt, Lithuania has been removed from China\'s customs registry, which prevents Lithuanian goods from getting customs clearance.\n“Lithuania has been crossed out [...], it seems that there\'s no such country in China\'s customs system,” it quotes Vidmantas Janulevičius, president of the Lithuanian Confederation of Industrialists.', '2021-12-02', 'https://www.lrt.lt/img/2021/12/02/1147964-786915-1287x836.jpg', 'www.lrt.lt'),
('https://www.macrumors.com/2021/12/02/ftc-lawsuit-block-nvidia-arm-acquisition/', 'U.S. Federal Trade Commission Sues to Block Nvidia\'s Planned Arm Acquisition', 'Juli Clover, Hartley Charlton, Joe Rossignol, Mitchel Broussard, Sami Fathi', 'planned, block, technology, commission, markets, federal, technologies, undermine, ftc, arms, chip, sues, acquisition, nvidia, arm, nvidias, trade', 'The United States Federal Trade Commission today announced that it has filed a lawsuit to block Nvidia from acquiring Arm in a deal worth $40 billion.\nThis proposed deal would distort Arm\'s incentives in chip markets and allow the combined firm to unfairly undermine Nvidia\'s rivals.\nAt the time, Nvidia said that it would use the Arm acquisition to create the \"world\'s premiere computing company for the age of AI.\"\nArm licenses its chip technology to more than 500 companies, including Apple, so there are major concerns around potential licensing changes.\nAccording to the lawsuit, an Nvidia acquisition of Arm could impact high-level advanced driver assistance systems, DPU SmartNICs for datacenter servers, and Arm-based CPUs for cloud computing service providers.', '2021-12-02', 'https://images.macrumors.com/t/VZVrnpt0fruX5wCWAbd8R_GXdE8=/1600x/article-new/2021/02/arm-logo-blue-bg.jpg', 'www.macrumors.com'),
('https://www.mathlingua.org', 'MathLingua', '', 'mathlingua', '', '2021-12-03', 'https://www.mathlingua.org/favicon.ico', 'www.mathlingua.org'),
('https://www.mattblaze.org/blog/faraday/', 'Matt Blaze: Testing Phone-Sized Faraday Bags', '', 'signal, strength, signals, faraday, measurements, blaze, matt, testing, db, pouch, attenuation, bags, phonesized, ghz, rf', 'So we want our Faraday pouch to provide at least that much attenuation at the frequencies of concern.\nThe instrument we used for our signal strength measurements was a Rhode and Schwarz model PR100 measurement receiver.\nNote that making signal strength measurements involves sending (low power) radio signals through the air between the signal generator and the receiver.\nIt\'s important to recognize that a Faraday pouch, no matter how effective, only prevents radio communication.\nMost of us almost certainly don\'t need a Faraday pouch.', '2021-12-03', 'https://www.mattblaze.org/photos/blog/faraday-cookieclosed-33-20211116-DSC00901.jpg', 'www.mattblaze.org'),
('https://www.mcgill.ca/newsroom/channels/news/synthetic-tissue-can-repair-hearts-muscles-and-vocal-cords-335206', 'Synthetic tissue can repair hearts, muscles, and vocal cords', '', 'engineering, vocal, students, hydrogel, guangyu, tissue, hearts, hydrogels, synthetic, injectable, mcgill, cords, test, muscles, repair', 'Combining knowledge of chemistry, physics, biology, and engineering, scientists from McGill University develop a biomaterial tough enough to repair the heart, muscles, and vocal cords, representing a major advance in regenerative medicine.\nThe same is true for vocal cords.\nThe team, led by Professor Luc Mongeau and Assistant Professor Jianyu Li, developed a new injectable hydrogel for wound repair.\nIllustration shows the use of injectable hydrogel as an implant to fill a wound and to restore the voice.\nVideo of Movie Clip Hydrogel PhonationThe vocal cord bioreactor simulates the biomechanics of vocal cords to test the hydrogels.', '2021-12-03', 'https://www.mcgill.ca/newsroom/files/newsroom/styles/wysiwyg_large/public/channels/image/vocal_cord_bioreactor.png?itok=9xSCU3c4', 'www.mcgill.ca'),
('https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/likely-cause-of-alzheimers-identified-in-new-study', 'Alzheimer’s: \'Breakthrough\' study finds likely cause', 'Hassan Yahaya', 'group, control, study, brain, mice, finds, alzheimers, disease, cause, likely, research, scientists, test, breakthrough', 'Using mouse models, researchers in Australia have identified one of the likely causes of Alzheimer’s disease.\nThe Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) estimate that up to 5.8 million people in the United States live with Alzheimer’s disease.\nThis inflammation occurred in both the test group and the control group, but it started at a much younger age in the test group.\nThese findings suggest explanations to long standing questions about the role of amyloid-beta in Alzheimer’s disease development.\n[…] These findings may have a significant global impact on the millions of people living with Alzheimer’s disease.”', '2021-12-03', 'https://post.medicalnewstoday.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/09/GettyImages-161145306_thumb.jpg', 'www.medicalnewstoday.com'),
('https://www.medrxiv.org/content/10.1101/2021.11.11.21266068v2', 'Increased risk of SARS-CoV-2 reinfection associated with emergence of the Omicron variant in South Africa', 'Juliet R.C. Pulliam, South African Dsi-Nrf Centre Of Excellence In Epidemiological Modelling, Analysis, Sacema, Stellenbosch University, South Africa, Pulliam Sun.Ac.Za, Http, Cari Van Schalkwyk, Nevashan Govender', 'omicron, increased, risk, reinfection, associated, emergence, variant, africa, south, sarscov2', '', '2021-11-11', 'https://www.medrxiv.org/sites/default/files/images/favicon.ico', 'www.medrxiv.org'),
('https://www.mh370search.com/2021/11/30/mh370-preliminary-findings/', 'MH370 GDTAAA Analysis', 'Richard Godfrey, David Burns, Dominik Bugmann, Ethan Larsen', 'wsprnet, technical, flight, analysis, gdtaaa, using, tracking, report, utc, mh370, findings, preliminary', 'The GDTAAA WSPRnet MH370 Analysis Preliminary Findings place the crash location at 33.177°S 95.300°E just 6 nm East of the 7th Arc.\nThe report can be downloaded hereThis preliminary report provides a summary of the key findings from the MH370 flight path analysis using the Global Detection and Tracking of Any Aircraft Anywhere (GDTAAA) software based on the Weak Signal Propagation Reporter (WSPR) data publicly available on the WSPRnet.\nThis report will be followed up by two papers.\nThe first paper will give all the findings every two minutes during the entire flight of MH370 from 7th March 2014 16:42 UTC to 8th March 2014 00:20 UTC.\nThe second paper will give the technical details of each detection of MH370 using the WSPRnet data and the technical details of the tracking of the MH370 flight path.', '2021-11-30', 'https://www.mh370search.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/MH370-Icon-150x150.png', 'www.mh370search.com'),
('https://www.michaelbromley.co.uk/blog/but-what-about-the-bus-factor/', 'But What About the Bus Factor?', 'Michael Bromley', 'community, risk, projects, work, contributors, im, factor, vendure, bus, project', 'The term “bus factor” refers to the number of project maintainers who, if hit by a bus and incapacitated, would cause that project to stall.\n~ 1) bus factor.\nSo what can I do to mitigate the bus factor risk?\nMitigation“I would simply raise the bus factor”The obvious mitigation is to raise the bus factor.\nShould merchants build their flashy new e-commerce apps on Vendure: bus factor one?', '2021-12-01', 'https://www.michaelbromley.co.uk/media/2021/12/romain-chollet-U3_QBX2qZb0-unsplash.jpg', 'www.michaelbromley.co.uk'),
('https://www.mothminds.com', 'Moth Minds: Fund individuals doing work you believe in', '', 'traditional, youre, fund, doing, individuals, moths, play, outside, means, believe, work, needs, inputs, world, moth, agency, minds', 'While “butterflies” sparkled within traditional systems, moths seemed to be playing games entirely of their own making.\nFrom the outside, agency is often misinterpreted as ambition, but I learned through observing these two types of people that they are actually quite different.\nAmbition means you\'re motivated to play games that others have already created in the world while agency means you\'re driven to play a game of your own.\nIt quickly became clear to me that our world desperately needs more niche moth-like perspectives and in turn, interesting, actualized visions of the future.\nIt just needs different inputs to produce the same infamous outputs: curiosity and creativity.', '2021-12-03', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/617f5127635b9a1a9a381527/61a2567a81dbc1226241ca42_Frame%2025.png', 'www.mothminds.com'),
('https://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-selects-companies-to-develop-commercial-destinations-in-space/', 'NASA Selects Companies to Develop Commercial Destinations in Space', 'Robert Margetta', 'destinations, nasa, companies, commercial, space, selects, develop', '', '2021-12-03', 'http://www.nasa.gov/sites/default/files/thumbnails/image/4e.jpg', 'www.nasa.gov'),
