('https://www.nature.com/articles/s41421-021-00329-3', 'Comprehensive investigations revealed consistent pathophysiological alterations after vaccination with COVID-19 vaccines', 'Liu, Shanghai Institute Of Stem Cell Research, Clinical Translation, Shanghai East Hospital, School Of Medicine, Tongji University, Shanghai, Wang, Key Laboratory Of Spine, Spinal Cord Injury Repair', 'fig, gene, vaccines, cell, expression, revealed, supplementary, covid19, pathophysiological, comprehensive, investigations, b, vaccination, alterations, cells, days, consistent, samples', 'By day 90, the profiles returned back to those before vaccination (Fig.\nUMAP distributions were drastically similar regardless of the different batches, suggesting minimal sequencing batch effects (Supplementary Fig.\nWe observed decreases in contents of CD4+ regulatory T cells (CD4.Treg), CD8+ T cells (CD8.T), and proliferating CD8+ cells (CD8.Tprolif) after vaccination (Fig.\n4: Subtype-specific differential gene expression and gene set overrepresentation analyses depicting common gene expression changes amongst different types of immune cells after vaccination.\nThe MVS scores were substantially higher after vaccination (Fig.', '2021-12-03', 'https://media.springernature.com/m685/springer-static/image/art%3A10.1038%2Fs41421-021-00329-3/MediaObjects/41421_2021_329_Fig1_HTML.png', 'www.nature.com'),
('https://www.nature.com/articles/s41586-021-04086-x', 'Advancing mathematics by guiding human intuition with AI', 'Davies, Deepmind, London, Veličković, Buesing, Blackwell, Zheng, Tomašev, Tanburn, Battaglia', 'intuition, z, mathematics, number, model, n, used, invariants, ai, intervals, function, knots, guiding, human, advancing, signature', 'The results of the subsequent stages will hold true only for the distribution P Z , and not the whole space Z.\nThe braids that we used were 4-braids (n = 11,756), 5-braids (n = 13,217) and 6-braids (n = 10,897).\nThe number of intervals in a symmetric group S N is O(N!2), which results in many billions of intervals in S 9 .\nThis has the added benefit of reducing the number of intervals per symmetric group (for example, to ~2.9 million intervals in S 9 ).\nModel and training procedureFor modelling the Bruhat intervals, we used a particular GraphNet architecture called a message-passing neural network (MPNN)48.', '2021-12-01', 'https://media.springernature.com/m685/springer-static/image/art%3A10.1038%2Fs41586-021-04086-x/MediaObjects/41586_2021_4086_Fig1_HTML.png', 'www.nature.com'),
('https://www.neowin.net/news/microsoft-says-its-own-edge-browser-is-more-trustworthy-than-so-2008-google-chrome/', 'Microsoft says its own Edge browser is more trustworthy than \"so 2008\" Google Chrome', 'Sayan Sen', 'technology, chrome, browser, 2008, microsoft, thats, edge, trying, google, trust, whats, trustworthy', 'Over the last few months, Microsoft appears to have become pretty desperate in trying to make people use its Edge browser more regularly.\nHere\'s the full message:Microsoft Edge runs on the same technology as Chrome, with the added trust of Microsoft.\nTo be completely fair to Microsoft, Google also occasionally sends such pop-ups and prompts when using its search engine or other services.\nMicrosoft Edge.\nAlso, when we search \"browser\" or \"browser download\" on Bing, recommendations for Edge pop up here as well as if Microsoft really wants people to notice its own web browser.', '2021-12-02', 'https://cdn.neow.in/news/images/uploaded/2021/05/1620415697_microsoft_edge_bug_1_story.jpg', 'www.neowin.net'),
('https://www.newstatesman.com/culture/books/2021/12/hg-wells-claire-tomalin-review', 'HG Wells and the human animal', 'John Gray Is An Author, Contributing Writer To The New Statesman., More This Author, John Gray', 'wellss, management, statesman, weekly, wells, hg, moura, world, tomalin, animal, human, life', 'Wells spent much of his life working to transform the human world into something better ordered, and more beautiful, than it had ever been before.\nIn his relationship with Moura, Wells realised he was no more a conscious individual than were the deluded masses.\nLike Shaw, Wells was enchanted by tyrants, seeing them as engineers of souls who could remould the wayward human animal.\nThe story reads today as a premonition of the attempts to remould the human animal that Wells foresaw, and in some moods supported, in the 20th century.\nHis most recent book is “Feline Philosophy” (Allen Lane)The Young HG Wells: Changing the WorldClaire TomalinViking, 272pp, £20', '2021-12-01', 'https://www.newstatesman.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/12/202148-HG-Wells-689x778.jpg', 'www.newstatesman.com'),
('https://www.nginx.com/blog/using-nginx-as-object-storage-gateway/', 'Using NGINX as an Object Storage Gateway', 'Elijah Zupancic Of', 'store, storage, configuration, gateway, nginx, object, api, using, docker, s3, plus', 'Using NGINX Plus as the S3 API gateway has some compelling benefits:Dynamic DNS resolution of upstreams using the NGINX Plus API – Whenever your S3 API domain changes its backing IP addresses, NGINX reconfigures automatically to use the new addresses.\nWe do not distribute a Docker image for NGINX Plus, because the image needs to incorporate your NGINX Plus credentials.\nFollow the instructions in the next section to build an NGINX Plus Docker image with the Dockerfile we provide, which includes settings for downloading the NGINX Plus binary.\nBuilding the NGINX Plus Gateway Docker ImageTo build the NGINX Plus Docker image, perform these steps:Clone the NGINX S3 Gateway project from our GitHub repo: git clone https://github.com/nginxinc/nginx-s3-gateway.git Change directory to nginx-s3-gateway: cd nginx-s3-gateway Copy your NGINX Plus certificate and key (nginx-repo.crt and nginx-repo.key) to the plus/etc/ssl/nginx subdirectory.\nNGINX Plus customers can find them at the F5 customer portal; if you are doing a free trial of NGINX Plus, they were provided with your trial package.', '2021-12-01', 'https://www.nginx.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/NGINX-object-storage-gateway_facebook.png', 'www.nginx.com'),
('https://www.nj.com/news/2021/12/he-bought-500-of-apple-gift-cards-at-target-scammers-wiped-them-clean-before-he-could-use-them.html', 'He bought $500 of Apple gift cards at Target. Scammers wiped them clean before he could use them.', 'Karin Price Mueller, Nj Advance Media For Nj.Com', 'cards, buy, scammers, apple, blum, wiped, gift, card, 500, target, clean, purchase, money, bought, didnt', 'This time last year, Mike Blum took advantage of a promotion at Target: Buy $100 worth of Apple gift cards and get a $20 Target gift card for free.\nIn the meantime, Blum said he’s frustrated to see retailers offer similar Apple gift card promotions this holiday season, and Blum wants to warn unsuspecting consumers.\n“After further research, we were able to confirm that your gift card was properly activated at the time of purchase,” Target said in an email.\nIf you’re buying a gift card in person, favor cards that retailers keep behind the counter or in a locked display case rather than stores that keep gift cards out in the open.\nBeyond that, there’s not much you can do other than buy gift cards online rather than off a store rack.', '2021-12-01', 'https://www.nj.com/resizer/JLBp8QxbebgT-O4xcwrfm4F5uYQ=/1280x0/smart/cloudfront-us-east-1.images.arcpublishing.com/advancelocal/JNZ4CFENFNHDLCBMZC5OT63VCA.jpg', 'www.nj.com'),
('https://www.npr.org/2021/11/30/1060025081/omicron-variant-netherlands-europe-south-africa', 'The omicron variant was in Europe a week before South Africa reported it', 'Bill Chappell', 'health, omicron, bans, nov, week, europe, travel, samples, africa, reported, south, variant', 'The omicron variant was in Europe a week before South Africa reported itEnlarge this image toggle caption Kenzo Tribouillard/AFP via Getty Images Kenzo Tribouillard/AFP via Getty ImagesThe omicron coronavirus variant was already in the Netherlands a week before South Africa reported the new variant to the World Health Organization, according to a Dutch health agency.\nRevelations about the variant\'s existence in Europe before it was reported in Africa add a new twist to questions about where and how the variant originated — and whether travel bans on South Africa and its neighbors are an appropriate response to the variant.\nSouth African President Cyril Ramaphosa says his country is being punished for detecting the variant and informing global health authorities about it.\nThe omicron variant triggered a rush of new travel restrictions targeting South Africa and other southern African nations.\n\"It could be that South Africa and Botswana saw it early because they have strong genetic sequencing networks.\"', '2021-11-30', 'https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2021/11/30/omicron-netherlands-first-case-africa_wide-8c0793bc132b5ff0fb660dafeb9623262e6c8c65.jpg?s=1400', 'www.npr.org'),
('https://www.npr.org/sections/health-shots/2021/12/01/1060141850/a-different-kind-of-covid-vaccine-is-about-ready-to-roll', 'A different kind of COVID vaccine is about ready to roll', 'Joe Palca', 'ready, vaccines, manufacturing, vaccine, different, duceygetty, authorization, subunit, karen, covid, protein, novavax, roll, kind, large', 'A different kind of COVID vaccine is about ready to rollEnlarge this image toggle caption Karen Ducey/Getty Images Karen Ducey/Getty ImagesA new kind of COVID-19 vaccine is about to roll out around the world.\nThese new vaccines are what\'s called protein subunit vaccines.\nAn advantage of protein subunit vaccines is they tend to be very stable, so they don\'t require freezers for storage.\nSanofi stumbled with its protein subunit vaccine, too.\nEnlarge this image toggle caption Karen Ducey/Getty Images Karen Ducey/Getty Images\"From a scientific perspective, it would be definitely great to have a subunit vaccine,\" he says.', '2021-12-01', 'https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2021/11/30/2021_11_30_novovax-1_wide-286009894ff73e4333bcd15988930b40a2fec728.jpg?s=1400', 'www.npr.org'),
('https://www.nytimes.com/2021/02/18/world/europe/silbo-gomero-canary-islands.html', '‘Special and Beautiful’ Whistled Language Echoes Around This Island', 'Raphael Minder', 'whistle, whistled, echoes, particularly, whistling, language, used, beautiful, whistlers, silbo, special, island, easy, residents, mr', 'Two whistlers might struggle to understand each other, particularly during their first encounters — and need to ask each other to repeat sentences — like strangers who speak the same language with different accents.\nBut “after whistling together for a while, their communication becomes as easy as if speaking Spanish,” Mr. Correa said.\nAs is the case in many languages, whether whistled or not, there is a generation gap on La Gomera.\nOlder residents on La Gomera recall how Silbo was used as a warning language, particularly when a police patrol was spotted searching for contraband.\nIn a recent fictional movie, “The Whistlers,” Silbo is used by gangsters as their secret code language.', '2021-02-18', 'https://static01.nyt.com/images/2021/02/03/world/00spain-whistling-dispatch-top-still/merlin_183062145_8478abd7-235c-4e56-9683-d58a393d5d39-facebookJumbo.jpg', 'www.nytimes.com'),
('https://www.nytimes.com/2021/11/23/business/dealbook/four-day-workweek.html', 'Is the Four-Day Workweek Finally Within Our Grasp?', 'Kevin J. Delaney', 'fourday, schedule, fridays, latest, workers, workweek, staff, pandemic, experiment, work, extend, finally, primary, grasp', 'This article is part of our latest DealBook special report on the trends that will shape the coming decades.\nBy December, the new schedule was working so well that Primary decided to extend it indefinitely.\nPrimary’s staff of 60 hasn’t taken pay cuts and workers aren’t expected to extend their hours during the four days when they work.\nThey occasionally do some work on Fridays, but are not expected to, and the day is meeting-free companywide.\nPrimary is part of the latest wave to experiment with a work schedule that has been proposed for decades but has never quite caught on.', '2021-11-23', 'https://static01.nyt.com/images/2021/11/28/multimedia/28sp-dealbook-workweek-shake/28sp-dealbook-workweek-shake-facebookJumbo.jpg', 'www.nytimes.com'),
('https://www.nytimes.com/2021/11/23/t-magazine/hayao-miyazaki-studio-ghibli.html', 'Hayao Miyazaki Prepares to Cast One Last Spell', 'Ligaya Mishan', 'read, wind, wings, war, prepares, rosso, father, factory, cast, spell, zero, true, hayao, miyazaki', 'But part of his films’ greatness is that they can also be loved by viewers who never sense the dark current below.\nIn a 1995 newspaper essay in The Asahi Shimbun, Miyazaki describes his father as something of a grifter, bribing officials to accept defective parts.\nLater, he briefly turned the factory into a dance hall, before bringing the family — Miyazaki is the second of four sons — back to Tokyo.\nThe Great Read Here are more fascinating tales you can’t help but read all the way to the end.\nAs Miyazaki grew older, he found fault with his father both for profiting off the war and for never expressing any shame or guilt.', '2021-11-23', 'https://static01.nyt.com/images/2021/11/24/t-magazine/24tmag-miyazaki-slide-FV6R-copy/24tmag-miyazaki-slide-FV6R-copy-facebookJumbo.jpg', 'www.nytimes.com'),
('https://www.nytimes.com/2021/12/02/technology/ftc-nvidia-arm-deal.html', 'F.T.C. Sues to Stop Blockbuster Chip Deal Between Nvidia and Arm', 'Cecilia Kang, Don Clark', 'technology, stop, push, blockbuster, federal, proposed, ftc, chip, sues, competition, regulators, rein, deal, arm, nvidia, trade', 'WASHINGTON — The Federal Trade Commission on Thursday sued to block Nvidia’s $40 billion acquisition of a fellow chip company, Arm, halting what would be the biggest semiconductor industry deal in history, as federal regulators push to rein in corporate consolidation.\nsaid the deal between Nvidia, which makes chips, and Arm, which licenses chip technology, would stifle competition and harm consumers.\nThe proposed deal would give Nvidia control over computing technology and designs that rival firms rely on to develop competing chips.\n“Tomorrow’s technologies depend on preserving today’s competitive, cutting-edge chip markets,” said Holly Vedova, the director of the F.T.C.’s competition bureau.\nThe action against the deal is the first major merger decision by the Federal Trade Commission under the leadership of Lina Khan, a critic of big corporate mergers and monopolies in technology.', '2021-12-02', 'https://static01.nyt.com/images/2021/12/02/multimedia/02chips/02chips-facebookJumbo.jpg', 'www.nytimes.com'),
('https://www.pcmag.com/news/reddit-goes-real-time-with-typing-indicators-comment-pills-more', 'Reddit Goes \'Real Time\' With Typing Indicators, Comment Pills, More', '', 'reddit, indicators, comment, realtime, real, website, pills, features, thread, platforms, reading, typing, goes, responding', 'Reddit says it wants to \"look and feel more lively and in the moment,\" so it\'s adding new features like voting and comment count animations, typing and reading indicators, and a new comment pill.\nThese indicators make sense on instant messaging platforms, for example, because they can dissuade people from talking over each other.\nBut they are part of Reddit\'s broader push to compete with other social platforms that have embraced real-time features to convince people to use their services more often.\nNow the core Reddit experience—reading and responding to discussion threads—will gain these pseudo-interactive features to \"help redditors connect in real time.\"\nReddit says the features are rolling out now on the platform\'s website as well as the official iOS and Android mobile apps.', '2021-12-03', 'https://i.pcmag.com/imagery/articles/0700JSkJQIIWnAJxPplUIiZ-1.fit_lim.size_1200x630.v1638476392.jpg', 'www.pcmag.com'),
('https://www.pcmag.com/news/trumps-social-media-site-quietly-admits-its-based-on-mastodon', 'Trump\'s Social Media Site Quietly Admits It\'s Based on Mastodon', '', 'admits, media, site, truth, archive, zip, trumps, social, quietly, based, code, source, platform, mastodon', 'To avoid a lawsuit, Donald Trump’s social media site is quietly acknowledging the computer code powering the platform comes from Mastodon.\nTrump’s “Truth Social” site now features a dedicated section labeled “open source,” which contains a Zip archive to Mastodon’s source code.\n(Truthsocial.com)Truth Social created the section on Nov. 12, two weeks after social networking provider Mastodon threatened to sue Trump’s platform for violating its open-source license.\nHowever, Trump’s social media site had claimed all of its source code was “proprietary,” and controlled solely by Truth Social.\nExpect Trump\'s social media platform to formally arrive in next year\'s first quarter.', '2021-12-03', 'https://i.pcmag.com/imagery/articles/06v9bAq2EXTDTovpWwCOh5f-1.fit_lim.size_1200x630.v1638393307.jpg', 'www.pcmag.com'),
('https://www.pnas.org/content/113/18/4900', 'What insects can tell us about the origins of consciousness', 'Andrew B. Barron, Macquarie University, Andrew.Barron Mq.Edu.Au, Colin Klein', 'information, tell, consciousness, capacity, system, origins, insect, midbrain, subjective, insects, structures, experience, sensory', 'Here we propose that at least one invertebrate clade, the insects, has a capacity for the most basic aspect of consciousness: subjective experience.\nWe therefore conclude that if subjective experience is indeed supported by midbrain structures in humans, then insects also have the capacity for a form of subjective experience.\nThis basic level has been termed primary consciousness (10), core consciousness (11, 12), phenomenal consciousness (13), or “I” consciousness (14).\nThe levels corresponding to these higher capacities are variously termed self-reflexive consciousness (7), access consciousness (13), higher-order awareness (10), or “me” consciousness (14).\nMoving Forward on Invertebrate Consciousness We have argued that insects possess a capacity for subjective experience.', '2016-05-03', 'https://www.pnas.org/content/113/18/4900/F1.large.jpg', 'www.pnas.org'),
('https://www.princeton.edu/news/2021/11/29/new-cancer-therapy-yibin-kangs-lab-holds-potential-switch-major-cancer-types', 'New cancer therapy from Yibin Kang\'s lab holds potential to switch off major cancer types without side effects', 'Photo By, Photo Flynn Larsen For Ludwig Cancer Research', 'kangs, switch, cancer, kang, lab, mtdh, gene, potential, types, holds, work, normal, yibin, important, major, breast, research, therapy', 'While 99% of breast cancer patients survive five years after diagnosis, only 29% do if the cancer has metastasized, according to current numbers from the National Cancer Institute.\n“Our work identified a series of chemical compounds that could significantly enhance the chemotherapy and immunotherapy response rates in metastatic breast cancer mouse models.\nAnd critically, if those mice did get breast cancer, they had significantly fewer tumors, and those tumors didn’t metastasize.\nThe project is just that challenging.”Kang compared the painstaking lab work to the endurance sports that he took up during the pandemic.\nThe research was supported by the Brewster Foundation, Ludwig Cancer Research, the Breast Cancer Research Foundation, the National Institutes of Health (R01CA134519), Department of Defense Breast Cancer Research Program (BC151403), the American Cancer Society, Susan G. Komen (PDF17332118) and the New Jersey Commission on Cancer Research (DFHS15PPCO21).', '2021-11-29', 'https://www.princeton.edu/sites/default/files/styles/scale_1440/public/images/2021/11/20171121_KangY_FINAL_DJA_010_retouched.jpg?itok=YXXAqqV4', 'www.princeton.edu'),
('https://www.protocol.com/bulletins/timnit-gebru-dair', 'Former Google AI ethicist Timnit Gebru launches her own AI institute', 'Aisha Counts, Nat Rubio-Licht, Allison Levitsky, Max A. Cherney, Lizzy Lawrence, Nick Statt, Issie Lapowsky, Anna Kramer, Kate Kaye, Tomio Geron', 'launches, fired, foundation, ethicist, work, gebrus, ai, press, release, google, timnit, institute, research, gebru', 'Timnit Gebru, who was fired by Google after raising concerns about the tech giant\'s AI work, has launched a new nonprofit organization called the Distributed Artificial Intelligence Research Institute.\nDAIR is a continuation of Gebru\'s activism against misuse of AI, and aims to be a home for \"community-rooted AI research free from Big Tech\'s pervasive influence,\" according to a press release on DAIR\'s website.\nThe institute is supported by the Ford Foundation, the MacArthur Foundation, the Kapor Center and the Open Society Foundation.\n“AI needs to be brought back down to earth,” said Gebru in the press release.\nWhen AI research, development and deployment is rooted in people and communities from the start, we can get in front of these harms and create a future that values equity and humanity.”', '2021-12-02', 'https://www.protocol.com/media-library/timnit-gebru.jpg?id=24901218&width=980', 'www.protocol.com'),
('https://www.protocol.com/workplace/stripe-hiring-issues-rescinded-jobs', 'Stripe is on a hiring spree. But it\'s also rescinding job offers and angering engineers.', 'Anna Kramer, Shen Lu, Bob Schukai, Bob Schukai Is Executive Vice President Of Technology Development, New Digital Infrastructure, Fintech At Mastercard, Where He Leads The Technical Design, Execution, Support Of Innovative Open Banking, Fintech Solutions', 'hiring, job, company, protocol, offer, spree, stripe, rescinding, process, tech, recruiter, angering, offers, engineers', 'But at the booming, much-revered payments company Stripe, some applicants have found themselves accepting job offers only to learn they have been rescinded without warning.\nProtocol also spoke with a former Stripe recruiter who described the company as embracing a “hire and fire” mentality and constantly shifting priorities and reorganizing staff.\nStripe is also not the only tech company to face problems with recruitment and hiring processes in the last year.\nFacebook spent the first quarter of 2021 battling one of its worst hiring crises in years, as engineers turned down job offers at unusually high rates and negative Glassdoor reviews spiked.\nOne technical manager — now employed elsewhere — described being approached by a Stripe recruiter when she took some time off of working.', '2021-12-01', 'https://www.protocol.com/media-library/stripe-building.jpg?id=28137544&width=1200&coordinates=0%2C334%2C0%2C334&height=600', 'www.protocol.com'),
('https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/blog/what-are-the-chances/202112/meditation-and-executive-attention', 'Meditation and Executive Attention', '', 'participants, attention, woollacott, printed, task, meditation, executive, pay, asked, meditators, stimulus', 'In concentrative meditation, meditators are asked to pay close attention to a specific object.\nEach time the meditator feels his or her attention wander, they are instructed to (gently) return their attention to it.\nThey selected these two forms of meditation because they thought that concentration meditation might be training practitioners to improve a form of attention that involves our ability to orient toward (pay attention to) a specific object.\nTesting AttentionTo test attention, you need a task that requires us to pay attention and one that we regularly make mistakes on.\nChan and Woollacott also tested concentrative meditation, asking participants to pay close attention to a specific object.', '2021-12-03', 'https://cdn2.psychologytoday.com/assets/styles/manual_crop_1_91_1_1528x800/public/field_blog_entry_images/2021-11/meditating_monk.jpg?itok=vvchIUAm', 'www.psychologytoday.com'),
('https://www.quad9.net/news/press/german-court-rules-against/', 'German Court Rules Against Internet Security Non-Profit Quad9 In First Hearing Versus Sony Music Germany', '', 'case, music, legal, internet, versus, gff, rules, sony, ruling, germany, dns, continue, injunction, rights, hearing, quad9, security, nonprofit', 'Quad9 filed an objection earlier this year, and as a result of this ruling Quad9 intends to continue opposition to the injunction in a higher court, and will move to appeal in a continuance.\n(GFF), eco Association of the Internet Industry (eco.de), and Stiftung Mercator Schweiz (stiftung-mercator.ch) in its defense, among others.\n\"The German Bundestag abolished the German interferer liability for Internet access providers years ago to facilitate the operation of open WIFIs.\nExposing the operators of recursive DNS resolvers to legal risks erodes the legal safeguards the law makers intended to establish.\"\nThe Quad9 DNS service is operated by the Swiss-based Quad9 Foundation, whose mission is to provide a safer and more robust Internet for everyone.', '2021-11-30', 'https://www.quad9.net/uploads/quad9_social_min_final_ce674aaced.png', 'www.quad9.net'),
('https://www.quantamagazine.org/quantum-simulators-create-a-totally-new-phase-of-matter-20211202/', 'Quanta Magazine', 'Charlie Wood', 'quanta, matter, simulators, magazine, cambridge, state, qubits, spin, quantum, neutral, groups, atoms', 'The key to building a quantum computer is to assemble a collection of qubits — quantum objects akin to classical bits — that satisfy two contradictory requirements.\n“That really matters.”Researchers have been using these grids of neutral atoms to probe phases of quantum matter.\nThe result is the first direct measurement of the topological order of a quantum spin liquid.\nNow quantum simulators are giving researchers the control necessary to thoroughly dissect a second example.\n“This probing of quantum spin liquids — in my view, it’s a very special moment,” Lukin said.', '2021-12-02', 'https://d2r55xnwy6nx47.cloudfront.net/uploads/2021/12/Quantum-Spin-Liquid_Kagome_1200_social_01.jpg', 'www.quantamagazine.org'),
('https://www.qubes-os.org/news/2021/11/17/qubes-4-1-rc2/', 'Qubes OS 4.1-rc2 has been released!', '', 'perform, os, youre, 41rc1, bugs, stable, candidate, users, release, released, 41, qubes, 41rc2', 'We’re pleased to announce the second release candidate for Qubes 4.1!\nQubes 4.1-rc2 contains fixes for bugs that were discovered in the first release candidate (4.1-rc1).\nFor existing Qubes 4.1-rc1 users, a regular update is sufficient to upgrade to 4.1-rc2.\nAs with any release candidate, it’s possible that user testing will reveal important bugs that we’ll want to fix before the stable release.\nWe plan to release the next release candidate in approximately five weeks.', '2021-11-17', 'https://www.qubes-os.org/attachment/icons/qubes-logo-icon-name-slogan-fb.png', 'www.qubes-os.org'),
('https://www.reuters.com/business/amazon-alabama-facility-ordered-re-run-union-election-us-labor-board-2021-11-29/', 'U.S. labor board official orders Amazon to redo union vote at Alabama warehouse', 'Julia Love Jeffrey Dastin, Julia Love, Jeffrey Dastin', 'decision, nlrb, board, rwdsu, warehouse, orders, official, workers, vote, alabama, organizing, amazon, company, redo, union, labor', 'In August, an NLRB hearing officer said the company\'s conduct around the previous vote had interfered with the election.\nThe decision for a redo adds pressure on Amazon, which has recently faced union campaigns in New York and Canada.\nWorker groups view organizing the company as a landmark goal that would invigorate the U.S. labor movement.\nIn Monday\'s decision, the NLRB regional director said that Amazon \"engaged in objectionable conduct that warrants setting aside the election.\"\nThe NLRB decision did not specify the second election\'s date or whether the vote will take place by mail or in person.', '2021-11-29', 'https://www.reuters.com/resizer/Ue8HZb61J3oAwPL-MJ2VeAb5a3k=/1200x628/smart/filters:quality(80)/cloudfront-us-east-2.images.arcpublishing.com/reuters/FP3FXFUWWVP7DMXOV34O62FSSE.jpg', 'www.reuters.com'),
('https://www.science.org/content/blog-post/omicron-time', 'Omicron Time', 'Derek Lowe', 'omicron, really, delta, thats, way, dont, data, sequence, immune, variant', 'So now we have the Omicron variant to think about.\nIf you look at a tree diagram, you can see that Omicron really jumps off by itself.\nWe don\'t see a lot of intermediate sequences, either, steps along the way to Omicron, even though these had to exist at some point.\nJust as before, you really, really need to get vaccinated, and you really, really need to get a booster if you can do that as well.\nWe sequence cases as much as we can to make sure that Omicron isn\'t drifting into something even more concerning.', '2021-12-03', 'https://www.science.org/apple-touch-icon.png', 'www.science.org'),
('https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/humans-are-doomed-to-go-extinct/', 'Humans Are Doomed to Go Extinct', 'Henry Gee', 'humans, species, rate, doomed, extinct, sapiens, world, living, economic, human, population, long, extinction', 'Stanford University biologist Paul Ehrlich’s book The Population Bomb was published in 1968, a year when the rate of world population growth was more than 2 percent—the highest in recorded history.\nThere is more genetic variation in a few troupes of wild chimpanzees than in the entire human population.\nAs well as being bad news for the millions of other species on our planet that rely on this matter, such sequestration might be having deleterious effects on human economic prospects.\nThe question is “How fast?”I suspect that the human population is set not just for shrinkage but collapse—and soon.\nTo paraphrase Lehrer, if we are going to write about human extinction, we’d better start writing now.', '2021-12-03', 'https://static.scientificamerican.com/sciam/cache/file/3D74552F-5C2E-48E4-8571AB514A4C7242.jpg', 'www.scientificamerican.com'),
('https://www.sfgate.com/local/article/Murders-of-crows-take-over-San-Francisco-Bay-Area-16667171.php', 'Murders of crows are taking over the Bay Area right now', 'Amanda Bartlett, Written By, Amy Graff, Tessa Mclean, Ariana Bindman, Susana Guerrero', 'crows, winter, taking, right, numbers, area, birds, theyre, phillips, san, murders, bay, food, francisco, count', 'Why are there so many crows in the Bay Area?\n“Winter roosts of crows can be quite spectacular — or terrifying if you’ve watched too many Hitchcock movies,” said Glenn Phillips, executive director of the Berkeley-based organization.\nThough people may have mixed feelings about the audacious and predatory birds, they’re here to stay — at least for a while.\nMost crows depart in the spring to nest and disperse into wider territory, which Phillips anticipates will happen in early March.\nLast year’s Christmas Bird Count in San Francisco tallied 1,520 crows — an increase from 738 crows in 2019 and 1,274 in 2018.', '2021-12-01', 'https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/23/04/42/21776535/3/rawImage.jpg', 'www.sfgate.com'),
('https://www.sifive.com/press/sifive-raises-risc-v-performance-bar-with-new-best-in-class', 'SiFive Raises RISC-V performance bar with New Best-in-Class SiFive Performance P650 Processor', '', 'p650, architecture, performance, bestinclass, sifive, ip, raises, market, bar, riscv, sifives, center, processor', 'The SiFive Performance P650 processor is expected to be the fastest licensable RISC-V processor IP core in the market, bringing RISC-V into new markets and applications, and will debut to lead partners in Q1 2022.\nThe SiFive Performance P650 processor IP represents our commitment towards relentless execution, delivering significant performance improvements in record time.\nThe SiFive Performance P650 processor builds upon the SiFive Performance P550 processor, maintaining an efficient core pipeline while expanding the processor instruction-issue width to deliver an impressive 40% performance increase per clock cycle(1).\nWith a projected score of 11+ SPECInt2006/GHz, the SiFive Performance P650 brings RISC-V into a new category of high-end computing applications.\nSiFive will offer an “Architecture Preview” to select lead customers, for evaluation of the SiFive Performance P650 ahead of general availability.', '2021-12-03', 'https://images.prismic.io/sifive/2980fa8f-a8a1-4175-9fd9-8cbf6d8719d0_SiFivePerformanceP650-2.png?auto=compress,format', 'www.sifive.com'),
('https://www.slashfilm.com/673162/heres-why-movie-dialogue-has-gotten-more-difficult-to-understand-and-three-ways-to-fix-it/', 'Here\'s Why Movie Dialogue Has Gotten More Difficult To Understand (And Three Ways To Fix It)', 'Ben Pearson', 'movie, mixing, difficult, gotten, sound, amc, theater, understand, film, mix, going, dialogue, level, heres, theaters, ways, fix, standard', 'And when the next feature came in the next week, the level was never reset, and now that level is playing way low for the regularly mixed movie.\nThe idea that a significant theater chain would purposefully ignore industry standards for something as crucial as sound is genuinely shocking.\nThankfully, I have not heard any similar stories about AMC Theaters, the largest theater chain in the United States.\nMeanwhile, Baker Landers thinks part of the trouble may have begun when theaters shifted away from projecting movies on film.\n\"We mix and release the film for the best case scenario, saying, \'This is how it should be.\'', '2021-11-30', 'https://www.slashfilm.com/img/gallery/is-it-just-me-or-has-movie-dialogue-gotten-more-difficult-to-understand/l-intro-1638206351.jpg', 'www.slashfilm.com'),
('https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/discovery-of-roman-dagger-leads-to-hundreds-more-artifacts-in-switzerland-180979122/', 'Amateur Archaeologist in Switzerland Unearths 2,000-Year-Old Roman Dagger', 'Smithsonian Magazine, David Kindy, Daily Correspondent, Read More, David Kindy Is A Daily Correspondent For', 'objects, unearths, site, archaeologist, dagger, amateur, 2000yearold, switzerland, schmid, rhaetian, near, gorge, tells, live, roman', 'Around 15 B.C.E., imperial Roman troops clashed with Rhaetian tribesmen near a gorge in Switzerland.\nThat’s where the ornate pugio remained until 2019, when an amateur archaeologist surveyed the site with a metal detector, reports Swiss Radio and Television (SRF).\n“It’s fair to say that this is certainly my most spectacular find to date,” Schmid tells Matthew Allen of SWI swissinfo.ch.\nAccording to archaeologists, the Roman dagger is in remarkably good condition.\n“Of course, I am pleased that what I have done has made a difference,” Schmid tells SRF, per Google Translate.', '2021-12-03', 'https://th-thumbnailer.cdn-si-edu.com/_CLrTJpMLYpN8mZLf1Nje64UuPU=/fit-in/1600x0/filters:focal(607x533:608x534)/https://tf-cmsv2-smithsonianmag-media.s3.amazonaws.com/filer_public/49/b4/49b48e86-c993-4996-bb2f-d04a3e13a602/roman_dagger.jpg', 'www.smithsonianmag.com'),
('https://www.statnews.com/2021/12/02/some-experts-suggest-omicron-variant-may-have-evolved-in-an-animal-host/', 'Some experts believe Omicron variant may have evolved in an animal host', 'Helen Branswell, Andrew Joseph, Marion Renault, Maddie Bender, Rachel Cohrs', 'omicron, think, sars2, infected, species, virus, believe, host, immunocompromised, animal, mutations, viruses, evolved, experts, variant', 'They speculate the virus could have evolved in another animal species.\nIn this new species, the virus evolved, accumulating roughly 50 mutations on the spike protein before spilling back over into people.\nA reverse zoonosis is when such a virus passes back into an animal species.)\nRobert Garry, a professor of microbiology and immunology at Tulane Medical School, has been tracking the SARS-2 mutations that have arisen.\nFor Worobey, the question is whether any animal species can become chronically infected with SARS-2 — in effect, whether there are animal species in which SARS-2 lingers in the way it does in immunocompromised people.', '2021-12-02', 'https://www.statnews.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/49666507451_dd60ed1bcf_h-1024x576.jpg', 'www.statnews.com'),
('https://www.synack.com/blog/this-microsoft-windows-rce-vulnerability-gives-an-attacker-complete-control/', 'This Microsoft Windows RCE Vulnerability Gives an Attacker Complete Control', 'Srt Community, Ryan Rutan, Peter Blanks', 'gives, client, data, attacker, remote, access, virtual, desktop, memory, machine, complete, buffer, vulnerability, windows, microsoft, control, rce', 'By Malcolm StaggCVE-2021-34535 is a Remote Code Execution (RCE) vulnerability in Remote Desktop Client, found by SRT member Malcolm Stagg earlier this year, and patched by Microsoft in August 2021.\nFinding the VulnerabilityI found this vulnerability by looking at the disassembly of several Windows dll’s in IDA debugger for potential memory access flaws.\nWhen raw pointers to memory buffers are used directly, it is easy to make a mistake that can lead to a serious memory access vulnerability.\nTSMF is a legacy plug-in for Remote Desktop, in which the Remote Desktop Server transfers a multimedia file to be played by the Remote Desktop Client.\nProtecting YourselfIf you’re accessing an untrusted virtual machine in Hyper-V or running an untrusted program on your virtual machine, disable “Enhanced Session Mode” whenever you can to reduce your attack surface.', '2021-11-24', 'https://cdnm.synack.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/malcolm-stagg-blog-top-image.jpg', 'www.synack.com'),
('https://www.theblockcrypto.com/post/126072/defi-protocol-badgerdao-exploited-for-120-million-in-front-end-attack', 'DeFi protocol BadgerDAO exploited for $120 million in front-end attack', '', 'attack, bitcoin, tokens, million, wrapped, badgerdao, used, frontend, end, users, exploited, protocol, defi, 120, stolen', 'DeFi protocol BadgerDAO has fallen victim to a large hack.\nAccording to security researchers PeckShield, $120.3 million was stolen from users of the protocol.\nBadgerDAO is a DeFi protocol focused on providing yield for bitcoin.\nThe idea is that you bridge your bitcoin over onto a smart contract platform like Ethereum, as wrapped bitcoin, which you can then use within DeFi applications.\nOne user had around 900 bitcoin ($50.8 million) worth of tokens stolen in a single transaction.', '2021-12-03', 'https://www.tbstat.com/wp/uploads/2021/11/211115_Hacker_General_.jpg', 'www.theblockcrypto.com'),
('https://www.thedrive.com/the-war-zone/43328/u-s-satellites-are-being-attacked-everyday-according-to-space-force-general', 'U.S. Satellites Are Being Attacked Every Day According To Space Force General', 'Joseph Trevithick, Tyler Rogoway', 'thompson, attack, satellite, attacks, air, day, force, space, russia, systems, satellites, attacked, according, general', 'DOD U.S. Space Force General David Thompson, Vice Chief of Space Operations, sits in a room at the Pentagon during a remote talk hosted by the Association of Old Crows in January 2021.\n“We’re really at a point now where there’s a whole host of ways that our space systems can be threatened.” \"Right now, Space Force is dealing with what Thompson calls \'reversible attacks\' on U.S. government satellites (meaning attacks that don’t permanently damage the satellites) \'every single day,\'\" according to Rogin.\nSpace Force was formally established as a separate branch within the Department of the Air Force in December of that year.\nUSAF Former Secretary of the Air Force Heather Wilson.\nUSAF Former Secretary of the Air Force Barbara Barrett during a ceremony unveiling the newly decorated Space Force hallway at the Pentagon in December 2020.', '2021-12-03', 'https://www.thedrive.com/content/2021/11/Satellite-tampering.jpg?quality=85', 'www.thedrive.com');
INSERT INTO `articles` (`url`, `title`, `authors`, `tags`, `summary`, `publish_date`, `image_url`, `domain`) VALUES
('https://www.theguardian.com/film/2021/dec/02/it-became-crystal-clear-they-were-lying-the-man-who-made-germans-admit-complicity-in-the-holocaust', '‘It became crystal clear they were lying’: the man who made Germans admit complicity in the Holocaust', 'Dorian Lynskey', 'complicity, admit, germans, man, final, holland, crystal, pope, lying, wanted, way, weyermann, film, clear, old, battsek, holocaust, account', '“Luke wasn’t consciously making a film,” Battsek says.\nIt’s a slow unravelling of someone’s tightly knitted personal history.”Margarete Schwarz, an interviewee in Final Account.\nPhotograph: © 2021 PM Final Account Holdings, LLC.\nKlaus Kleinau in Final Account.\nThat may ultimately prove to be a more enduring legacy than Final Account itself.', '2021-12-02', 'https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/35845c2be63c620e333ef71c943d17b70789b33d/0_239_4601_2762/master/4601.jpg?width=1200&height=630&quality=85&auto=format&fit=crop&overlay-align=bottom%2Cleft&overlay-width=100p&overlay-base64=L2ltZy9zdGF0aWMvb3ZlcmxheXMvdGctZGVmYXVsdC5wbmc&enable=upscale&s=b7e8139f051983b0fb0f720a1f5631ec', 'www.theguardian.com'),
('https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2021/dec/01/the-urinary-leash-how-the-death-of-public-toilets-traps-and-trammels-us-all', 'The urinary leash: how the death of public toilets traps and trammels us all', 'Emine Saner', 'local, health, urinary, trammels, traps, leash, loos, women, death, toilets, loo, need, men, public, toilet', 'Of its survey of more than 3,000 Londoners, more than 90% said it was difficult to find a public toilet.\nThe decline won’t stop until we legally require them, and it’s quite shocking that there is no legislation to require public toilets.\n“But of course it made it worse.” When public toilets were closed en masse during the lockdowns, people were defecating in parks and on beaches.\nThe loss of public toilets also means, says Jyotsna Vohra, the director of policy at the Royal Society for Public Health (RSPH), “the burden falls disproportionately on people experiencing other health inequalities.\nHopefully we wouldn’t, but being British we might.” Public toilets could be designed by the best architects and become attractions in their own right, she says.', '2021-12-01', 'https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/6403c22512993b9f016b19d18e7cd0c6160e40f1/0_199_3000_1800/master/3000.jpg?width=1200&height=630&quality=85&auto=format&fit=crop&overlay-align=bottom%2Cleft&overlay-width=100p&overlay-base64=L2ltZy9zdGF0aWMvb3ZlcmxheXMvdGctZGVmYXVsdC5wbmc&enable=upscale&s=16d3bf264842663423641e6e8739702e', 'www.theguardian.com'),
('https://www.theguardian.com/world/2021/dec/02/how-probable-omicron-covid-variant-take-hold-uk', 'How probable is it Omicron Covid variant will take hold in UK?', 'Nicola Davis', 'omicron, africa, early, day, sgene, uk, probable, cases, covid, hold, south, variant', 'Omicron is causing consternation around the world, with the variant found to be behind an exponential rise in Covid cases in South Africa.\nOne issue is that there are important differences that make it difficult to compare the situations in South Africa and beyond.\nWith Covid already “running hot” in the UK and some European countries, picking up early signs of Omicron’s impact is challenging.\nBefore the new variant was detected, Covid cases in South Africa were very low, meaning its impact became clear at an early juncture.\nOthers have also stressed that the situation in the UK is in its early days, but there are reasons for concern.', '2021-12-02', 'https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/afc8b64a44a1b758f4262dc45e4f143117897b74/0_203_3501_2101/master/3501.jpg?width=1200&height=630&quality=85&auto=format&fit=crop&overlay-align=bottom%2Cleft&overlay-width=100p&overlay-base64=L2ltZy9zdGF0aWMvb3ZlcmxheXMvdGctZGVmYXVsdC5wbmc&enable=upscale&s=25efd440eff1bd5cc6c0d93ebaa22707', 'www.theguardian.com'),
('https://www.thelancet.com/journals/lanepe/article/PIIS2666-7762(21)00258-1/fulltext?s=08#%20', 'The epidemiological relevance of the COVID-19-vaccinated population is increasing', 'Günter Kampf, Guenter.Kampf Uni-Greifswald.De, Singanayagam A, Hakki S, Dunning J, Shitrit P, Zuckerman Ns, Mor O, Gottesman Bs, Chowers M.', 'transmission, epidemiological, covid19vaccinated, covid19, week, increasing, 2021, patients, unvaccinated, vaccinated, cases, vaccination, population, fully, relevance', 'Recent data, however, indicate that the epidemiological relevance of COVID-19 vaccinated individuals is increasing.\n12 of 31 infections in fully vaccinated household contacts (39%) arose from fully vaccinated epidemiologically linked index cases.\nIn Germany, the rate of symptomatic COVID-19 cases among the fully vaccinated (“breakthrough infections”) is reported weekly since 21.\nOctober 2021 ( Figure 1 ) providing clear evidence of the increasing relevance of the fully vaccinated as a possible source of transmission.\nFourteen fully vaccinated patients became severely ill or died, the two unvaccinated patients developed mild disease [].', '2021-12-03', 'https://els-jbs-prod-cdn.jbs.elsevierhealth.com/cms/asset/105856cd-4b52-403a-90e8-c31ecbf52065/gr1.jpg', 'www.thelancet.com'),
('https://www.theverge.com/2021/12/2/22812641/jack-dorsey-twitter-facebook-amazon-zuckerberg-bezos-congress-resign', 'As tech founders resign, Congress loses its favorite targets', 'Makena Kelly, Dec', 'favorite, dorsey, founders, ceo, companies, political, loses, company, twitter, social, congress, resign, tech, targets, lawmakers', 'On Monday, Twitter CEO Jack Dorsey announced that he would be stepping down from the company he co-founded over 15 years ago.\nAnd like every other major tech CEO, Dorsey has dutifully testified, even if just as an excuse for lawmakers to yell at him for “censoring” them without achieving tangible results.\nThis wave has already caught up with older tech companies.\nAt that point in time, “Democrats viewed tech as their industry,” said Adam Kovacevich, founder and CEO of Chamber of Progress, a tech industry group.\n“I think that it’ll actually deprive the entire conversation without the political theater of these hearings.”For now, the pressure on tech companies continues.', '2021-12-02', 'https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/P09BdZNBvgY46jhLbXgy47hzDNQ=/0x146:2040x1214/fit-in/1200x630/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23058216/acastro_211130_4903_0003.jpg', 'www.theverge.com'),
('https://www.theverge.com/22807858/tiktok-influencer-microsoft-excel-instagram-decoder-podcast', 'How an Excel TikToker manifested her way to making six figures a day', 'Nilay Patel, Nov', 'think, tiktoker, youre, really, excel, day, making, things, thats, manifested, way, different, business, im, figures, going', 'I don’t want to give too much away because it’s all in the interview, but I think you’re really going to like this one.\nThere’s cool things happening too: I was reading about different things with Microsoft Teams that will make that realm more virtual.\nI think I’m going to start advertising on YouTube, but for me, the course sales make so much more sense.\nI’m going to get these courses out in the next few weeks and then I want to see how big it’s scaling.\nI’m really just scaling from here — scaling holiday season, Black Friday, doing it up, seeing where we land Q1 2022.', '2021-11-30', 'https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/dq_qx94VJgqWUO-wz870zke7mJQ=/0x148:2050x1221/fit-in/1200x630/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23052402/VRG_ILLO_Decoder_Kat_Norton_s.jpg', 'www.theverge.com'),
('https://www.theverge.com/22811740/qualcomm-snapdragon-8-gen-1-always-on-camera-privacy-security-concerns', 'Qualcomm’s new always-on smartphone camera is a potential privacy nightmare', 'Dan Seifert, Dec', 'alwayson, qualcomm, nightmare, privacy, qualcomms, smartphone, feature, using, looking, potential, phones, system, camera, heape, phone', 'But while those features may sound neat and perhaps even convenient, I’m not convinced that having an always-on camera is worth the tradeoff in privacy concerns.\nThe always-on camera features are discussed at hour three of Qualcomm’s four-hour presentation introducing the Snapdragon Gen 1 system-on-chip.\nQualcomm is framing the always-on camera as similar to the always-on microphones that have been in our phones for years.\nAn always-on camera is a step beyond the always-on microphones already in our phonesIt’s true that smart home products already have features like this.\nThe always-on camera is part of a chain that includes a new low-power image signal processor (ISP) and a machine learning step.', '2021-12-01', 'https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/kvPOB80TTQ8OKkuNn9OC3REMCQE=/0x146:2040x1214/fit-in/1200x630/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19085113/akrales_190819_3594_0298.jpg', 'www.theverge.com'),
('https://www.theverge.com/c/22807871/apple-frontline-employees-retail-customer-service-pandemic', 'Apple’s frontline employees are struggling to survive', 'Zoe Schiffer', 'apple, told, wasnt, frontline, apples, survive, customers, work, customer, employee, retail, store, employees, struggling', '“People get emotional,” says a current retail employee in Pennsylvania.\nApple’s retail employees make on average between $19 and $25 an hour in the United States, according to Glassdoor.\nThat’s good for the retail industry, but can be grating for employees who want to build a career at the tech giant.\nIn the store, Apple uses something called a “net promoter score” to see how stores are performing.\nIn 2017, Apple customers with older iPhones realized that if they replaced their phone batteries, the performance would significantly improve.', '2021-11-01', 'https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/1xuROSCF9PgT_sAu9qVrpgzMBes=/204x320:2796x1681/fit-in/1200x630/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23049951/VRG_Illo_4894_Apple_Lede_Still.jpg', 'www.theverge.com'),
('https://www.tomshardware.com/news/raspberry-pi-releases-legacy-os', 'Raspberry Pi Releases \'Legacy\' OS to Target Bullseye Problems', 'Ian Evenden', 'products, os, support, bullseye, raspberry, version, target, software, pi, legacy, supported, release, problems, releases', 'Raspberry Pi is releasing a new, old, version of its operating system, Raspberry Pi OS Legacy, to tackle problems and incompatibilities encountered in the recent transition to a new version based on Debian Bullseye.\n(Image credit: Tom\'s Hardware)As we reported at the time, Raspberry Pi OS Bullseye came with a free speed boost for certain Raspberry Pi models, a new window manager, and a host of problems not limited to library and HAT compatibility, video drivers, and with camera modules.\nThe new Legacy release claims to fix all that.\nThe legacy OS sticks with version 5.10 of the Linux kernel, and branches the firmware too, so won’t support any future products.\n“Although we will not support new products on the legacy image, we will make sure any new revisions of older products continue to be supported,” writes Raspberry Pi director of software engineering Gordon Hollingworth on the Raspberry Pi website.', '2021-12-02', 'https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/ES6NWBt8LweLV36rHaDtPJ-1200-80.jpg', 'www.tomshardware.com'),
('https://www.tweag.io/blog/2021-12-02-nix-cas-4/', 'Implementing a content-addressed Nix', '', 'goal, build, return, nix, implementing, state, self, derivation, contentaddressed, output, set, derivations', 'Although the feature is still marked as experimental, the release of Nix 2.4 marks the entry of content-addressed derivations in a released Nix version.\nSo our buildDerivation should actually be redefined asdef buildDerivation ( derivation : Derivation ) - > Set [ Realisation ] : remainingOutputs = tryToSubstituteOutputs ( derivation ) if ( remainingOutputs == [ ] ) : return buildInputs ( ) return buildResolvedDerivation ( Derivation .\nSomething like:def buildDerivation ( derivation : Derivation ) - > Set [ Realisation ] : remainingOutputs = tryToSubstituteOutputs ( derivation ) if ( remainingOutputs == [ ] ) : return buildInputs ( ) newRealisations = buildResolvedDerivation ( Derivation .\nThe interface of a Goal , is essentially:class Goal : State = Callable [ [ Goal ] , None ] state : State dependencies : [ Goal ] def amDone ( self ) - > None : .\nThis means that the relatively complex logic needed to build content-addressed derivations has been pretty painful to implement.', '2021-12-02', 'https://tweag.io/logo.png', 'www.tweag.io'),
('https://www.twilio.com/blog/cold-war-numbers-station-twilio-voice-python-flask', 'Create a Cold War-Era Numbers Station with Twilio Voice and Python Flask', '', 'number, youll, message, flask, using, cold, warera, station, numbers, glitch, code, file, twilio, voice, create, python', 'Put on your fedora and dark glasses, because you’re about to become a Cold War-era numbers station operator!\nEncrypt your message Now that you have a way to store and retrieve your original message, you’ll need a way to encrypt it.\nIf you don\'t currently own a Twilio phone number with voice call functionality, you\'ll need to purchase one.\nTest your webhook Call your Twilio number from a mobile device or landline, and you should hear a lot of numbers being read out to you.\nIf we were using the raw Twilio Voice HTTP API, we could do some pretty nifty stuff here by decorating the text with SSML tags.', '2021-12-03', 'https://twilio-cms-prod.s3.amazonaws.com/original_images/On-QJfvswwhzTdLXOG524L1zD87NxsvxGprffW3HdbXIqI7oO2KyhvAXSoeaYQbusbcTHLc_xk4Avs', 'www.twilio.com'),
('https://www.usnews.com/news/news/articles/2021-12-01/new-dinosaur-species-from-chile-had-a-unique-slashing-tail', 'New Dinosaur Species From Chile Had a Unique Slashing Tail', 'Associated Press, Dec., At A.M.', 'slashing, tails, unique, vargas, chile, science, end, stegosaurus, stegouros, tail, dinosaur, species, weapon', 'By SETH BORENSTEIN, AP Science WriterFossils found in Chile are from a strange-looking dog-sized dinosaur species that had a unique slashing tail weapon, scientists reported Wednesday.\n“It’s a really unusual weapon,” said Vargas, a University of Chile paleontologist.\nIt just looks crazy.”The plant-eating critter had a combination of traits from different species that initially sent paleontologists down the wrong path.\nThe back end, including its tail weapon, seemed similar to a stegosaurus, so the researchers named it stegouros elengassen.\nFrom bird-like snout to tail tip, stegouros stretched about six feet (two meters) but would only come up to the thighs of humans, Vargas said.', '2021-12-01', 'https://www.usnews.com/dims4/USNEWS/6868977/2147483647/thumbnail/970x647/quality/85/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fmedia.beam.usnews.com%2F13%2F9e736d989ca84d823363345a5dbba9%2Fmedia%3A8a611f21145a4156b153c49f68c2ea01Bizarre_Dinosaur_48293.jpg', 'www.usnews.com'),
('https://www.vanityfair.com/style/2021/10/how-the-fbi-discovered-a-real-life-indiana-jones-in-indiana', 'How the FBI Discovered a Real-Life Indiana Jones in, of All Places, Rural Indiana', 'Condé Nast, Josh Sanburn, Leonardo Santamaria, Joshua Hunt', 'jones, archer, millers, indiana, miller, skulls, rural, carpenter, agents, items, places, reallife, discovered, remains, collection, fbi', 'He took them into the basement, where Archer saw the collection he’d been imagining for months.\nCarpenter noticed Miller only had the skulls and asked where the bodies were.\nIn the barn, agents found more bags of bones and skulls, some that had sat there for 50 years, never opened.\nAt the beginning, Carpenter says Miller watched the agents as they carted off his collection.\nBy then the FBI had seized 2,000 bones and 5,000 cultural artifacts and funerary objects out of a total collection of 42,000 items.', '2021-10-19', 'https://media.vanityfair.com/photos/6169fc9704af8a6b309603e6/16:9/w_1280,c_limit/VF1121_Archeology_Thief_Site_Story_Image.jpg', 'www.vanityfair.com'),
('https://www.vice.com/en/article/bvnn3a/i-lost-dollar400000-almost-everything-i-had-on-a-single-robinhood-bet', 'I Lost $400,000, Almost Everything I Had, on a Single Robinhood Bet', '', 'single, really, stupid, told, money, options, lost, investing, dont, 400000, bet, lot, robinhood', 'Then the $5,000 became $15,000 when I bet on something else, then it became $50,000 when I bet on silver.\nLooking at all of TipRanks, my understanding was that this was a very, very safe bet with a limited amount of risk.\nAdvertisementThen I just went all in on this one single stock option: The $200 strike price call option on Alibaba.\nI feel like the younger folks are really, really stupid, especially folks who have money now.\nWhen I lost the money, the things that I regretted were actually not losing the money.', '2021-12-03', 'https://video-images.vice.com/articles/61a7ce0ea06c9d009387965a/lede/1638388454887-gettyimages-1250406928.jpeg?image-resize-opts=Y3JvcD0xeHc6MC44NDI3eGg7MHh3LDAuMDAzOHhoJnJlc2l6ZT0xMjAwOiomcmVzaXplPTEyMDA6Kg', 'www.vice.com'),
