('https://yuval-alaluf.github.io/hyperstyle/', 'HyperStyle', '', 'support, weights, video, format, latent, generator, does, tag, image, hyperstyle', 'We propose HyperStyle, a hypernetwork that learns to modulate StyleGAN\'s weights to faithfully express a given image in editable regions of the latent space.\nBy learning this mapping, HyperStyle efficiently predicts the desired generator weights in less than 2 seconds per image, making it applicable to a wide-range of applications.\nWe additionally demonstrate that even after modifying the pre-trained generator weights, HyperStyle preserves the appealing structure and semantics of the original latent space and generator.\nHyperStyle generalizes well to out-of-domain images, even when unobserved during the training of the hypernetwork or generator.\nThis hints that HyperStyle does not only learn to correct flawed attributes, but rather learns to refine the generator in a more general sense.', '2021-12-03', 'https://yuval-alaluf.github.io/hyperstyle/images/thumbnail.jpg', 'yuval-alaluf.github.io');
